n=North Macedonia\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n|togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|feb}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div>\n\n|altlbl1=Active cases\n\n|collapsible=y\n|data=\n2020-02-26;;;1;;;1;+1;firstright1=y\n;;;1;;;1;;;collapsed=y;id=feb\n2020-03-06;;;3;;;3;+2;+200%\n2020-03-07;;;3;;;3;+0;+0%\n2020-03-08;;;4;;;4;+1;+33%\n2020-03-09;;;7;;;7;+3;+75%\n2020-03-10;;;7;;;7;+0;+0%\n2020-03-11;;;9;;;9;+2;+29%\n2020-03-12;;;9;;;9;+0;+0%\n2020-03-13;;;13;;;13;+4;+44%\n2020-03-14;;;19;;;19;+6;+46%\n2020-03-15;;;19;;;19;+0;+0%\n2020-03-16;;1;24;;;24;+5;+26%\n2020-03-17;;1;36;;;36;+12;+50%\n2020-03-18;;1;48;;;48;+12;+33%\n2020-03-19;;1;67;;;67;+19;+40%\n2020-03-20;;1;85;;;85;+18;+27%\n2020-03-21;;1;94;;;94;+9;+10%\n2020-03-22;1;1;114;;;114;+29;+22%\n2020-03-23;2;1;136;;;136;+22;+19%\n2020-03-24;2;1;148;;;148;+12;+9%\n2020-03-25;3;1;177;;;177;+29;+20%\n2020-03-26;3;3;201;;;201;+24;+14%\n2020-03-27;3;3;219;;;219;+18;+9%\n2020-03-28;4;3;241;;;241;+22;+10%\n2020-03-29;6;3;259;;;259;+18;+7%\n2020-03-30;7;12;285;;;285;+26;+10%\n2020-03-31;9;12;329;;;329;+44;+15%\n2020-04-01;10;17;354;;;354;+25;+8%\n2020-04-02;11;17;384;;;384;+30;+8%\n2020-04-03;12;20;430;;;430;+46;+12%\n2020-04-04;17;20;483;;;483;+53;+12%\n2020-04-05;18;23;555;;;555;+72;+15%\n2020-04-06;21;27;570;;;570;+15;+3%\n2020-04-07;26;30;599;;;599;+29;+5%\n2020-04-08;29;37;617;;;617;+18;+3%\n2020-04-09;30;37;663;;;663;+46;+7%\n2020-04-10;32;41;711;;;711;+48;+7%\n2020-04-11;34;41;760;;;760;+49;+7%\n\n|caption='''Sources:'''\n* {{Cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/info-COVID-19.pdf|title=Ministry of Health, North Macedonia|language=mk}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[North Macedonia]] in February 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sitel.com.mk/ushte-tri-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-vkupnata-brojka-dostigna-sedum|title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043c|website=\u0421\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b \u0422\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref>\nThe initial contagion in the country was mainly connected with the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy]] as there are circa 70,000 residents<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comuni-italiani.it/statistiche/stranieri/mk.html|title=Macedoni in Italia|website=comuni-italiani.it|language=it}}</ref>  of [[Italy]] from [[North Macedonia]] and due to a mass hysteria about the virus itself there was a mass returning to [[North Macedonia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/dva-novi-potvrdeni-sluchai-na-korona-virus-vo-debar/|title=\u0414\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440|date=6 March 2020|website=zdravstvo.gov.mk|language=mk-MK|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n===February 2020===\nOn '''26 February''', [[North Macedonia]] confirmed its first case of SARS-CoV-2, a 50-year-old woman that got tested at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases in [[Skopje]]. She had been in [[Italy]] for a month and was sick for two weeks. Upon returning to North Macedonia, she immediately reported herself to the clinic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/prv-sluchaj-na-zabolen-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=2020-02-26|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/china-coronavirus-outbreak-latest-updates-200226003835539.html|title=First case of coronavirus confirmed in North Macedonia|date=26 February 2020|publisher=Al Jazeera|url-status=live|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> This case was isolated and didn't lead to further infections.\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\n===March 2020===\nOn '''6 March''', two more cases were confirmed positive: a married couple from [[Balanci]], [[Centar \u017dupa]], who were residents of [[Brescia]], [[Italy]], and presumably returned to the country out of fear of the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sitel.com.mk/dva-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-0|title=\u0414\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=6 March 2020|website=Sitel|language=mk|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> They entered North Macedonia on 27 February and went to the clinic in [[Debar]] on 2 March. They were not initially tested for SARS-CoV-2, but when their symptoms were getting worse they were tested on 6 March. After getting positive results, the couple was transferred to the Clinic in Skopje to be taken care of.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.giornaledibrescia.it/brescia-e-hinterland/da-brescia-alla-macedonia-due-positivi-al-coronavirus-1.3465324/|title=Da Brescia alla Macedonia, due positivi al coronavirus|date=7 March 2020|website=Giornale di Brescia|language=it|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''9 March''' the number of infected people in the country increased to 7 - three family members of the cases registered on 6 of March and Nina Caca Biljanovska, the director of the Clinic for Skin Diseases in Skopje. Biljanovska's case caused controversy, as she did not self-isolate after returning from a vacation in Italy. Moreover, she had continued going to work and was a speaker at a conference attended by 100 people before getting tested. The Minister of health subsequently fired her.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%d0%b2%d0%ba%d1%83%d0%bf%d0%bd%d0%be-%d1%81%d0%b5%d0%b4%d1%83%d0%bc%d0%bc%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%b7%d0%b0%d1%80%d0%b0%d0%b7%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%be%d0%b4-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%be%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%b2/|title=\u0412\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e \u0441\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043c\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0441\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0458\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0443\u0436\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043e\u0434 \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440|last=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=9 March 2020|website=\u041c\u0410\u041a\u0424\u0410\u041a\u0421|language=mk-MK|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%D1%84%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%BF%D1%87%D0%B5-%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B0-%D0%B7%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D1%81%D0%BE-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80/|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u0414\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u045c\u0435 \u0431\u0438\u0434\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430|date=10 March 2020|publisher=Makfax|url-status=live|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''10 March''', after a formal request from the mayor of [[Debar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/sovetot-na-debar-bara-iten-prekin-na-nastavata-vo-uchilishtata-poradi-koronavirusot/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0438\u0442\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0438\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442|date=10 March 2020|website=Telma|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> (the city where 5 of the 7 cases were found)  and the controversies regarding Biljanovska the Ministry of Health of North Macedonia implemented stronger measures to prevent further spreading of the virus, including a temporary two week closure of all education institutes (from kindergartens to universities), prohibition of traveling to the most infected countries ([[China]], [[Korea]], Italy, [[France]], [[Germany]], etc.), prohibition of all public events and closure of sport events to the public.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/vonredni-merki-na-vladata-protiv-korona-virusot/?__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=b51217bf8577b4a88a9e253e58ed1549698a59bb-1583919165-0-AYI8DAACqOSWx00wOsG9XHQJ6T-3Ij5mCw1_NyCmHJqry57wZy6H91IU7fSJACpVP-jrwKDVzyiF1Tt3vxapMcyM9wf70QUZ9heDY2lq5hbDyPf0Je1DWcxSD5WoFDWhQJu1wiPT_ot30lue_-WSFLX67PiFSJRIHoRL5VCW7O776sBBbU35c_GV8zfR8nJ07uiynPY2A85FYiyMq3YzVNi1R2-xN6JGMXifXD5ZL0uOe-VyWPSBHicd8DI4TYhSI5p_44h_3fe78aEhqN_zbJOzBQwv1BRRiaSuD6gRcyijmuHLxXibBkzytCyKdpmzHqrMeOPT4csXMV6E2LxI76E|title=\u0412\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442|date=10 March 2020|website=Telma|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> Later that day the first case was confirmed to tested negatively on the repeated coronavirus test. The patient, however, is still recovering in the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novamakedonija.com.mk/featured/%D0%B2%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%BE%D1%82-%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%81%D1%82-%D0%B7%D0%B0-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B2%D0%BE%D0%B7%D0%B0/|title=\u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u0435 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0435\u043d|date=10 March 2020|website=NovaMakedonija|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> \n\n[[File:SARS-Covid2 Quarantined areas in North Macedonia.png|thumb|Quarantined areas on 13 March in red]]\n\nOn '''11 March''' two more cases were confirmed positive, both from Debar<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/dvajca-novi-zaboleni-od-koronavirus/|title=\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441|date=11 March 2020|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> They are related to the first cases registered in the town.\n\nOn '''13 March''' four more cases were confirmed positive. As all 4 were from Debar, the Government declared a [[state of emergency]] in the municipalities of Debar and  Centar \u017dupa. All movement inside and outside the two quarantined municipalities was banned; only people living there were allowed to return to their homes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.mk/a/30486178.html|title=\u041a\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u0438 \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440 \u0416\u0443\u043f\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442, \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0437\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435|date=13 March 2020|website=slobodnaevropa.mk|language=mk-MK|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Later on, President Pendarovski made a decision on the engagement of the Army in affected areas in Debar and Centar \u017dupa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%bf%d1%80%d0%b5%d1%82%d1%81%d0%b5%d0%b4%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b5%d0%bb%d0%be%d1%82-%d0%bf%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b4%d0%b0%d1%80%d0%be%d0%b2%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d0%b4%d0%be%d0%bd%d0%b5%d1%81%d0%b5-%d0%be%d0%b4/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0435 \u041e\u0434\u043b\u0443\u043a\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0430\u043d\u0433\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0410\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u0438 \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440 \u0416\u0443\u043f\u0430|date=13 March 2020|website=alsat-m.tv|language=mk-MK|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Also it was announced that entries of foreign nationals to the country arriving from 'high-risk countries' would start getting denied.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-heath-coronavirus-northmacedonia/north-macedonia-bars-foreigners-arriving-from-high-risk-countries-over-coronavirus-idUSKBN2101NI?fbclid=IwAR0K-J4_hgAb5COQ6LxvQyV6kro6gdjpnZFgEinZ_L96HXJZsaKaavBz1UY|title=North Macedonia bars foreigners arriving from 'high-risk countries' over coronavirus|publisher=[[Reuters]]|date=13 March 2020|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''14 March''', 8 people were tested for coronavirus, 6 of which returned positive (5 from Debar and one from Skopje returning from a trip to [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]). A total of 14 of the patients were hospitalized at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases in Skopje, while the 5 new cases from Debar remained in the local hospital.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 \u0448\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 18 |url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%d0%b2%d0%b8%d0%b4%d0%b5%d0%be-%d1%83%d1%88%d1%82%d0%b5-%d1%88%d0%b5%d1%81%d1%82-%d0%bb%d0%b8%d1%86%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%be/ |website=Makfax |accessdate=14 March 2020 |language=mk |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''16 March''', 7 persons (5 officially) were positive (4 from Debar, 1 from Skopje and two tested in a private clinic). The patient in [[Skopje]] had just returned from a trip to the [[Netherlands]] via [[Vienna]], the two additional cases tested positive in the private [[Filip II Hospital, Skopje|\u017dan Mitrev Hospital]]. They got retested by the public laboratory the following day and their positive results got confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0414\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 7 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430, \u0442\u0440\u043e\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435! |url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%b4%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b5%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b0-%d0%b2%d0%ba%d1%83%d0%bf%d0%bd%d0%be-7-%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%bd%d0%b8/ |website=Alsat-m |accessdate=16 March 2020 |language=mk |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Because of the increased number of cases, both domestically and globally, the Government of North Macedonia decided to close the two international airports (Skopje and Ohrid) and ban foreigners from entering the country. The ban does not affect diplomats and medical personnel (which are required to obtain permission from the Ministry of Interior) and truck drivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nezavisen.mk/se-zatvoraat-megjunarodniot-aerodrom-skopje-i-site-kopneni-granichni-premini/|title=\u0421\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0430\u0442 \u041c\u0435\u0453\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0430\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0440\u043e\u043c \"\u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435\" \u0438 \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043f\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438|publisher=nezavisen.mk|date=16 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''17 March''' 5 new positive cases were confirmed - 4 in Debar (two nurses and two doctors, one of whom was Arben Agolli, former mayoral candidate and political activist<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://republika.mk/vesti/makedonija/personalot-pozitiven-na-korona-ambulantata-vo-debar-pod-karantin/ |title = \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0435\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430, \u0430\u043c\u0431\u0443\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u043f\u043e\u0434 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d - \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430}}</ref>) and one in Skopje, raising the number to 32.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/ushte-pet-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=Telma|date=17 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref> Political leaders decided to postpone the early parliamentary elections scheduled for 12 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mk.voanews.com/a/5332708.html|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u045c\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u043e\u0434\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0430\u0442|publisher=VOA News|date=17 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''18 March''', 4 new cases were confirmed positive, all of them Macedonian citizens from Skopje coming from [[Belgium]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://centar.mk/blog/2020/03/18/novi-chetiri-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-zemjava-site-se-od-skopje/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430, \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435|publisher=Centar.mk|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> [[Prime Minister of North Macedonia|Prime Minister]] [[Oliver Spasovski]] announced that the Government is considering declaring a State of Emergency in the country, something that had never happened before.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kanal5.com.mk/vladata-pobara-voveduvanje-vonredna-sostojba-vo-celata-drzhava/a413682|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0432\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0434\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u0430|publisher=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b 5|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> The State of Emergency was officially declared by the President later the same day and following this event, since the Parliament was dismissed, the Government gained legislative and executive power.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nezavisen.mk/pendarovski-proglasi-vonredna-sostojba/|title=\u041f\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430|publisher=Nezavisen|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> Later that day 7 more people were tested positive on the virus (4 in Skopje and 3 in Debar).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sitel.com.mk/ushte-7-pozitivni-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-brojot-na-bolni-se-iskachi-na-42|title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 7 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0447\u0438 \u043d\u0430 42|publisher=\u0421\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''19 March''', 6 new cases were confirmed positive: 3 in Debar, 1 in Skopje, 1 in [[Gostivar]], and 1 in [[\u0160tip]]. The case from Gostivar is a Macedonian citizen coming from [[Switzerland]], the case from \u0160tip is a 4-year-old that got infected at a kindergarten in [[England]] and the rest are domestic citizens related to previously confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kanal5.com.mk/mz-do-16-chasot-shest-novi-sluchai-so-koronavirus-megju-niv-i-chetirigodishno-devojche-zarazeno-vo-gradinka-vo-anglija/a413930|title=\u041c\u0417: \u0414\u043e 16 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0442 \u0448\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u043c\u0435\u0453\u0443 \u043d\u0438\u0432 \u0438 \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u043d\u043e \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0458\u0447\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u043e \u0432\u043e \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0410\u043d\u0433\u043b\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b 5|date=19 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''20 March''', 19 new cases, all of them in Skopje, were confirmed positive. 17 of them were tested at the private [[Filip II Hospital, Skopje|\u017dan Mitrev Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://press24.mk/mz-19-novozaboleni-od-koronavirus-brojkata-na-dijagnosticirani-pacienti-vo-zemjata-e-67-lica|title=\u041c\u0417: 19 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 - \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0435 67 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=press24.mk|date=20 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> With this outbreak Skopje surpassed Debar in number of confirmed cases. Later the same day 3 people tested positive (2 in Skopje and 1 in \u0160tip). One of the people from Skopje said that she had travelled to [[Serbia]] before she was confirmed positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv21.tv/mk/novi-tri-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-sega-brojkata-e-70/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0435 70|publisher=TV 21|date=20 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> Again, later the same day 6 new cases tested positive (4 in Skopje and a married couple in [[Kavadarci]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kanal5.com.mk/shest-novozaboleni-lica-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-vkupno-76-lica-do-21-00-chasot/a414184|title=\u0428\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430,\u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 76 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0434\u043e 21.00 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0442|publisher=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b 5|date=20 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''21 March''', 9 new cases were confirmed positive: 7 in Skopje and 2 in \u0160tip.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82-%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8-%D1%81%D0%BB%D1%83%D1%87%D0%B0%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81-%D0%B2%D0%BE-%D0%B7%D0%B5/|title=\u0414\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u2013 \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 85 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438|publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=21 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> Later the same day the Government imposed a [[curfew]] as a protection measure against the virus outbreak. The curfew will be in the place everyday starting 22 March from 9 p.m. to 6 a.m.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ako.mk/%d0%be%d0%b4-%d1%83%d1%82%d1%80%d0%b5-%d1%81%d0%b5-%d0%b2%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b5%d0%b4%d1%83%d0%b2%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%bb%d0%b8%d1%86%d0%b8%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d1%87%d0%b0%d1%81-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%bc%d0%b0/|title=\u041e\u0434 \u0443\u0442\u0440\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0432\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0447\u0430\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043e\u0434 21 \u0434\u043e 6 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0442|publisher=\u0410\u043a\u043e.\u043c\u043a|date=21 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''22 March''', 29 new cases were confirmed positive: 22 in Skopje, 3 in \u0160tip, 2 in Debar, 1 in [[Ohrid]], and 1 in Kumanovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/brojkata-na-zaboleni-od-koronavirus-vo-zemjava-dostigna-114-lica/|title=\u0411\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 114|publisher=A1on|date=22 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref> On 22 March, North Macedonia recorded the first fatality, \u0430 57-year-old woman from [[Kumanovo]] that was confirmed positive to the virus [[postmortem]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vecer.mk/node/484671|title=\u041f\u0420\u0412 \u0421\u041c\u0420\u0422\u0415\u041d \u0421\u041b\u0423\u0427\u0410\u0408 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440|date=22 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''23 March''', 22 new cases were confirmed positive: 15 in Skopje, 4 in Debar, 2 Kumanovo, and 1 in Ohrid.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://republika.mk/vesti/makedonija/potvrdeni-ushte-22-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vkupnata-brojka-sega-e-136/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0443\u0448\u0442\u0435 22 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u0435 136|publisher=\u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430|date=23 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> The same day the second death was confirmed, a 63-year-old man from Debar that was hospitalized in Skopje on 17 March, reportedly his situation was stable and he suddenly got in a bad state in the night when he was attached to a respiratory machine but that wasn't enough.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%D0%B2%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80-%D1%81%D0%BC%D1%80%D1%82%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D1%81%D0%BB%D1%83%D1%87%D0%B0%D1%98-%D0%BE%D0%B4-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81-%D0%B2%D0%BE-%D0%BC/|title=\u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0441\u043c\u0440\u0442\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=23 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''24 March''', 12 new cases were confirmed positive: 7 in Skopje and 5 in Kumanovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mkd.mk/makedonija/obrazovanie-i-zdravstvo/12-novi-zarazeni-od-koronavirus-vkupniot-broj-dostigna-148-lica|title=12 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 148 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=\u041c\u041a\u0414.\u043c\u043a|date=24 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''25 March''', 29 new cases were confirmed positive: 20 in Skopje and 3 in Kumanovo, 3 in [[Veles, North Macedonia|Veles]], 2 in [[Prilep]], and 1 in Debar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/29-novi-sluchai-na-zarazeni-od-koronaviruv-vkupno-177-zaboleni/|title=29 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0432, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 177 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438|publisher=\u0422\u0435\u043b\u043c\u0430|date=25 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref> The same day the \"Patient zero\" of the outbreak in [[Debar]], the wife of the couple from Balanci that tested positive on 6 March was confirmed as the third death case. She was 66 years old. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.mk/a/30509237.html|title=\u0422\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u0436\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442, \u0434\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0443\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u043a\u0435\u043d\u0434|publisher=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0421\u043b\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430|date=25 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''26 March''', 24 new cases were registered positive: 15 from Skopje, 4 from Kumanovo, 2 from Debar, and 1 from Ohrid and \u0160tip each, as well as the first case from Tetovo. 2 patients recovered.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://360stepeni.mk/novi-24-zarazeni-so-kornavirus-vkupnata-brojka-vo-zemjava-iznesuva-201-litse/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 24 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 201 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0435|publisher=360 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438|date=26 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''27 March''', 18 new cases were registered positive: 11 from Skopje, 4 from Prilep, 2 from Kumanovo, and 1 from Tetovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://360stepeni.mk/filipche-brojkata-na-zaboleni-od-kornoavirus-shto-ja-spodeluvame-e-tselosno-tochna-vo-momentov-iznesuva-219/|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u0411\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0448\u0442\u043e \u0458\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u0435 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e \u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u2013 \u0432\u043e \u043c\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 219|publisher=360 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438|date=27 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''28 March''', 22 new cases were confirmed positive: 9 in Skopje, 3 in Kumanovo and Struga each; 2 in Tetovo, Prilep, and Debar each; and 1 in Bitola. Also it was confirmed the fourth death case, a 66 years old woman from Struga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/registrirani-22-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-zemjata-pochina-edna-zhena-od-okolinata-na-struga/|title=\u041f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u0442\u0440\u0443\u0448\u043a\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, 22 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430|publisher=A1on|date=28 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> \n\nOn '''29 March''', 18 new cases were confirmed positive: 6 in \u0160tip, 3 in Skopje, 3 in Veles, 2 in Struga, 1 in Strumica, 1 in Debar, 1 in Tetovo, and 1 in [[Gevgelija]]. Also two new death cases, a 31-year-old and 91-year-old men were confirmed today.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%d0%b2%d0%ba%d1%83%d0%bf%d0%bd%d0%be-257-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%be%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%b2%d0%b8%d1%80%d1%83%d1%81-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%bc%d0%b0%d0%ba%d0%b5/|title=\u0412\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 259 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0430 6 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=29 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''30 March''', 26 new cases were confirmed positive: 19 in Skopje, 3 in Kumanovo, 1 in Prilep, 1 in Tetovo, 1 in Debar, and 1 in [[Kriva Palanka]]. The seventh death was recorded, a 79 years old man from Debar, while 9 patients recovered (8 from Skopje and 1 from Debar).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sdk.mk/index.php/makedonija/osum-meditsinski-litsa-i-dvajtsa-patsienti-se-pozitivni-na-koronavirus-od-skopskiot-zavod-za-rehabilitatsija/|title=\u041e\u0441\u0443\u043c \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043e\u0434 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434 \u0437\u0430 \u0440\u0435\u0445\u0430\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=sdk.mk|date=30 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''31 March''' the Ministry of Health announced 44 new cases: 23 in Kumanovo, 11 in Skopje, 5 in Tetovo, 2 in Prilep, 2 in Struga, and 1 in Prilep. A 45-year-old man from Kumanovo and a 78-year-old man from Debar, both with pre-existing conditions, passed away. Up to that day 3,518 tests were made.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/registrirani-44-novi-sluchai-vkupnata-brojka-na-dijagnosticirani-iznesuva-329-lica-na-klinikata-za-infektivni-bolesti-i-febrilni-sostojbi-pochinaa-2-lica/|title=\u0420\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 44 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438-\u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 329 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430, \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0438 \u0444\u0435\u0431\u0440\u0438\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0430 2 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=zdravstvo.gov.mk|date=31 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===April 2020===\nOn '''1 April''' the Ministry of Health announced 25 new positive cases: 7 in Kumanovo, 7 in Skopje, 4 in Tetovo, 3 in [[Bitola]], 2 in Struga, 1 in Gevgelija and 1 in Ko\u010dani. A 64-years-old woman from Struga with pre-existing conditions, passed away. It was also discovered that a 66-years-old woman, also from Struga, who had died a day before tested positive on the post mortem test. 5 patients recovered as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/potvrdeni-25-novi-sluchai-pozitivni-na-pozitivni-na-kovid-19-vkupnata-brojka-na-dijagnosticirani-iznesuva-354-na-infektivnata-klinika-vo-skopje-pochina-pacientka-od-labunishta/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 25 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434 19-\u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 354, \u043d\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u041b\u0430\u0431\u0443\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0430|publisher=zdravstvo.gov.mk|date=1 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://iph.mk/covid19-31-3-2020/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0441\u043e covid-19 \u0432\u043e \u0440\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u2013 31.03.2020|publisher=iph.mk|date=1 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''2 April''', 30 new cases were registered positive: 12 from Skopje, 9 from Prilep, 8 from Kumanovo, and 1 from Kriva Palanka.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tera.mk/%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-30-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%b4%d1%80%d0%b6%d0%b0%d0%b2%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b0-%d0%be%d0%b4-%d0%bd%d0%b8%d0%b2-9-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%bf%d1%80%d0%b8%d0%bb/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 30 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0434\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430, \u043e\u0434 \u043d\u0438\u0432 9 \u0432\u043e \u041f\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043f|publisher=\u0422\u0435\u0440\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=2 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''3 April''', 46 new cases were registered positive: 23 from Kumanovo, 13 from Skopje, 2 from Debar, 2 from Veles, 2 from Gevgelija, 2 from Tetovo, 1 from Prilep and 1 from Gostivar. One more death was also confirmed: a 68-years-old man from the villages around Tetovo. In the evening, another suspected fatality was confirmed to be positive for Covid-19, a 70-years-old man from Kumanovo. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libertas.mk/pochinatiot-paczient-od-kumanovo-na-infektivnata-klinika-vo-skop%d1%98e-pozitiven-na-kovid-19/?__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=c8a88d72c45f43925ac6624a1936112617beb2ca-1585944904-0-AT5POI2mwfEY3A7x0TPkrvr7dVuTJZE_91hUdMjd5Ylcc6Eoq0kAJ6n5O7YDLAjObwKDZ15VbTBV2ssYWh2HntrapMBiWQNzrN8KZbmyzmLPFz3WYqeUSSHM4Ne-X5GshNLqzZWhdjzskkchrr5TRbaxCt8Z6eaDJm9tVYAcqo6FUGeH8Tta4CbJDfEHvkXWuIonLU-fwDoHoOFlSMDK3mG62ejVdVNT1Za_yjiJ3zHLToDaDV-ZPOnV5f1YzgMU_-XLANAfdmInqbtsegG4a3OEZCbhOer4MERO1f5j9VCrmLVsvE_oFryFKPbDu9mOtJ1ikRLdx173_bWbGu4_I3DOqjdlkw3ZtsAkS-ew3gHjGUR0nTe1nFCxDaqM1CYLL46UW-rHq5ZQte6RZlf_D6I|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u0443\u043c\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0418\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435 - \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0435\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-199|publisher=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0422\u0412|date=3 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''4 April''', 53 new cases were registered positive: 14 from [[Struga]], 13 from Skopje, 8 from Kumanovo, 6 from [[Ko\u010dani]], 5 from \u0160tip, 2 from Prilep, Tetovo and Gostivar each and 1 from Veles. Also five new death cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/5-%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b8-%d0%b8-53-%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8%d0%b4-19-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%b7%d0%b5/|title=5 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438 \u0438 53 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-19 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430|publisher=\u0410\u043b\u0441\u0430\u0442-\u041c|date=4 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''5 April''', 72 new cases were registered positive: 21 from Kumanovo, 14 from Skopje, 11 from Tetovo, 9 from Prilep, 7 from Ko\u010dani, 2 from Kru\u0161evo, Bitola and Radovi\u0161 each, 1 from Struga, Veles, Gostivar and \u0160tip each. Also one new case was confirmed dead, a 63-year-old man from Struga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://opserver.mk/makedonija/novi-72-sluchaja-pozitivni-na-koronavirus-eden-pochinat-dosega-vkupno-555-zaboleni/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=novi-72-sluchaja-pozitivni-na-koronavirus-eden-pochinat-dosega-vkupno-555-zaboleni|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 72 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442, \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 555 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 |publisher=\u041e\u043f\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0435\u0440 |date=5 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Later the same day the Institute of Public Health of the Republic of North Macedonia corrected the previously announced numbers by cities in term that one case from Gostivar is a citizen returning from Slovenia quarantined in Gostivar but lives in Strumica and one case from Tetovo is a citizen returning from abroad who is quarantined in Tetovo but lives in Radovi\u0161.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makpress.mk/Home/PostDetails?PostId=339670|title=\u0418\u0408\u0417 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0432\u043e \u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e \u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0440 \u0441\u0435 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0435\u045a\u0435 |publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0441 |date=5 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''6 April''', 15 new cases were registered positive: 8 in Kumanovo, 4 in Skopje and 1 in Tetovo, Struga and \u0160tip each. Also it was confirmed three new death cases: a 69-year-old and 65-years-old men from Tetovo and a 40-year-old man from Ko\u010dani. 6 patients recovered as well. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://kurir.mk/makedonija/vesti/raste-brojot-na-zrtvi-i-zarazeni-vo-makedonija-koronavirus-imaat-570-lica/|title=\u0420\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0438 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438: \u0412\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u0430\u0442 570 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=\u041a\u0443\u0440\u0438\u0440|date=6 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''7 April,''' 29 new cases were registered positive: 15 in Skopje, 7 in Kumanovo, 3 in Struga and Ko\u010dani each and 1 in Prilep. It was also confirmed 5 new deaths: a 52 and 53-years-old men from Kumanovo, an 81-year-old woman from \u0160tip,  a 65-year-old woman from Struga and a 62-year-old woman from Tetovo. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kajgana.com/novi-29-zarazeni-i-5-smrtni-sluchai-od-covid-19|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 29 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0438 5 \u0441\u043c\u0440\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043e\u0434 COVID-19|date=2020-04-07|website=\u041a\u0430\u0458\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> Later that day, it was confirmed one more death. A 45-year-old man from Skopje heading towards the City General hospital \"8th September\" for treatment. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.kajgana.com/pochina-45-godishen-skopjanec-zarazen-od-koronavirus-na-pat-kon-bolnicata-8-septemvri|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 45-\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0446 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u043d \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430\u0442\u0430 \"8 \u0421\u0435\u043f\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0432\u0440\u0438\"|date=2020-04-07|website=\u041a\u0430\u0458\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nOn '''8 April''', 18 new cases were registered positive: 7 in Skopje, 4 in Prilep, 2 in Bitola and Kumanovo each, 1 in Kru\u0161evo, Ko\u010dani and Kavadarci. Two new deaths were also confirmed, a 73-year-old man from Kumanovo, and the one positive case from Kavadarci. He was a 44 year old foreign citizen found dead in his apartment, who was tested postmortem. 7 patients recovered as well. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/info-covid-19-do-7-april.pdf|title=\u0421\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0441\u043e covid-19 \u0432\u043e \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u2013 07.04.2020|date=2020-04-08|website=zdravstvo|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Later that same day, one more death was confirmed. A 27-year-old woman from Kumanovo which, while infected, gave birth on the 30th of March. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kajgana.com/pochina-rodilkata-od-kumanovo-pozitivna-na-covid-19|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043b\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u0443\u043c\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 COVID-19|date=2020-04-08|website=\u041a\u0430\u0458\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nOn '''9 April''', 46 new cases were registered positive: 13 in Kumanovo, 12 in Skopje, 8 in Prilep and Veles each, 2 in Struga and 1 in Tetovo, Ko\u010dani and Probi\u0161tip each. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%b0%d1%86%d0%b8%d0%b5%d0%bd%d1%82-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b5%d0%bd-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8%d0%b4-19-%d1%80%d0%b5/|title=\u0420\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 46 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-19|publisher=\u0410\u043b\u0441\u0430\u0442-\u041c|date=9 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''10 April''', 48 new cases were registered positive: 25 in Kumanovo, 11 in Skopje, 4 in Prilep, 3 in Struga, 2 in Gostivar and 1 in Ohrid, \u0160tip, and Tetovo each. Two new deaths were also confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%b0-%d0%b4%d0%b2%d0%b0%d1%98%d1%86%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%b0%d1%86%d0%b8%d0%b5%d0%bd%d1%82%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-2/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0430 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-19|publisher=\u0410\u043b\u0441\u0430\u0442-\u041c|date=10 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''11 April''', 49 new cases were registered positive: 14 in Kumanovo, 13 in Skopje, 8 in Prilep, 6 in \u0160tip and Veles each and 1 in Gostivar and Ko\u010dani each. Two new deaths were also confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://puls24.mk/%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-49-%d0%b7%d0%b0%d1%80%d0%b0%d0%b7%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%b8-%d0%b4%d0%b2%d0%b0%d1%98%d1%86%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b8-%d0%be%d0%b4-%d0%ba%d0%be/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 49 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u041e\u0420\u041e\u041d\u0410\u0412\u0418\u0420\u0423\u0421\u041e\u0422 \u0432\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 24 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0430.|publisher=\u041f\u0443\u043b\u0441 24|date=11 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:COVID-19 outbreak in North Macedonia (April 11th).png|thumb|COVID-19 outbreak in North Macedonia (April 11th)]]\n\n== Prevention measures ==\nPreparatory measures against a potential outbreak started in late January 2020. National measures against the pandemic are led by health minister [[Venko Filip\u010de]] and the Commission for Infectious Diseases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sdk.mk/index.php/makedonija/podgotveni-sme-za-koronavirusot-nema-potreba-od-panika-veli-ministerot-za-zdravstvo-filipche/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0434\u0433\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043c\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442, \u043d\u0435\u043c\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430, \u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435|publisher=SDK |date=31 January 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nStarting from 27 January, thermal cameras installed at the [[Skopje Airport]], started monitoring passengers coming from [[Istanbul]] and [[Dubai]] who serve as links to [[China]], which was at the moment the epicenter of the epidemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.mk/a/30397586.html|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u0411\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430, \u0430\u043c\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0443\u0442\u0440\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442 |publisher=slobodnaevropa.mk |date=26 January 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Following the first meeting with [[WHO]] representative Jihane Tawilah, the country's preparedness for early detection & stopping the spread of the virus was assessed as satisfactory. Health minister Venko Filip\u010de announced that North Macedonia's healthcare system is completely prepared for a potential outbreak. In addition to the thermal cameras, information leaflets were distributed to police stations and the custom checks at all border passes.\n\nOn 4 February, the first reagents to detect the virus were imported from [[Ni\u0161]], [[Serbia]]. Filip\u010de said that at the moment the country had about 40.000 surgical masks and medical protective suits, but additional procurement was considered to prepare the country for a potential outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fokus.mk/filipche-ne-postoi-nitu-eden-somnitelen-sluchaj-za-korona-virus-vo-zemjava/|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u041d\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438 \u043d\u0438\u0442\u0443 \u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430 |publisher=Fokus |date=4 February 2020|language=mk|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Worldwide Coronavirus Map] \u2013 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE)\n* [https://koronavirus.gov.mk/en/media-center Latest information on COVID-19 and measures for prevention of spreading issued by the Government] - Official information about the Coronavirus in North Macedonia.\n* [https://gdi-sk.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/2096bd4b051b42948ac3f5747e80c3a5 Status Map, North Macedonia] - GIS Map of all cases North Macedonia.\n\n{{Portal bar|Medicine|Europe|North Macedonia}}\n\n{{2019-nCoV|state=expanded}}\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Current event|2=current pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in North Macedonia}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in North Macedonia<br>{{small|''\u041f\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 2020'' (in Macedonian)}}\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in North Macedonia.svg\n| legend1         = {{center|Map of regions with confirmed (red) coronavirus cases (as of 4 April)}}\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[North Macedonia]]\n| first_case      = [[Skopje]]\n| arrival_date    = 26 February 2020 <br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=2|day1=26|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]] via [[Italy]]\n| recovery_cases  = 41\n| deaths          = 34\n| confirmed_cases = 760\n<ref>{{cite web |url=https://koronavirus.gov.mk/en/media-center |title=Latest information on COVID-19 in North Macedonia|website=koronavirus.gov.mk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gdi-sk.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html?fbclid=IwAR0Dd9MY7njiNtDkPpPt8R2SeD4pW_6TO12axwKrT4CcegckY4P4Ezt43f4#/2096bd4b051b42948ac3f5747e80c3a5|title=Real-time Coronavirus condition in North Macedonia|website=gdi.net|language=mk-MK}}</ref>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = [https://koronavirus.gov.mk/ koronavirus.gov.mk]\n| Status Map      = https://gdi-sk.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/2096bd4b051b42948ac3f5747e80c3a5\n}}\n\n<onlyinclude>\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=wdmd\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=North Macedonia\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n|togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|feb}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div>\n\n|altlbl1=Active cases\n\n|collapsible=y\n|data=\n2020-02-26;;;1;;;1;+1;firstright1=y\n;;;1;;;1;;;collapsed=y;id=feb\n2020-03-06;;;3;;;3;+2;+200%\n2020-03-07;;;3;;;3;+0;+0%\n2020-03-08;;;4;;;4;+1;+33%\n2020-03-09;;;7;;;7;+3;+75%\n2020-03-10;;;7;;;7;+0;+0%\n2020-03-11;;;9;;;9;+2;+29%\n2020-03-12;;;9;;;9;+0;+0%\n2020-03-13;;;13;;;13;+4;+44%\n2020-03-14;;;19;;;19;+6;+46%\n2020-03-15;;;19;;;19;+0;+0%\n2020-03-16;;1;24;;;24;+5;+26%\n2020-03-17;;1;36;;;36;+12;+50%\n2020-03-18;;1;48;;;48;+12;+33%\n2020-03-19;;1;67;;;67;+19;+40%\n2020-03-20;;1;85;;;85;+18;+27%\n2020-03-21;;1;94;;;94;+9;+10%\n2020-03-22;1;1;114;;;114;+29;+22%\n2020-03-23;2;1;136;;;136;+22;+19%\n2020-03-24;2;1;148;;;148;+12;+9%\n2020-03-25;3;1;177;;;177;+29;+20%\n2020-03-26;3;3;201;;;201;+24;+14%\n2020-03-27;3;3;219;;;219;+18;+9%\n2020-03-28;4;3;241;;;241;+22;+10%\n2020-03-29;6;3;259;;;259;+18;+7%\n2020-03-30;7;12;285;;;285;+26;+10%\n2020-03-31;9;12;329;;;329;+44;+15%\n2020-04-01;10;17;354;;;354;+25;+8%\n2020-04-02;11;17;384;;;384;+30;+8%\n2020-04-03;12;20;430;;;430;+46;+12%\n2020-04-04;17;20;483;;;483;+53;+12%\n2020-04-05;18;23;555;;;555;+72;+15%\n2020-04-06;21;27;570;;;570;+15;+3%\n2020-04-07;26;30;599;;;599;+29;+5%\n2020-04-08;29;37;617;;;617;+18;+3%\n2020-04-09;30;37;663;;;663;+46;+7%\n2020-04-10;32;41;711;;;711;+48;+7%\n2020-04-11;34;41;760;;;760;+49;+7%\n\n|caption='''Sources:'''\n* {{Cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/info-COVID-19.pdf|title=Ministry of Health, North Macedonia|language=mk}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[North Macedonia]] in February 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sitel.com.mk/ushte-tri-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-vkupnata-brojka-dostigna-sedum|title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043c|website=\u0421\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b \u0422\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref>\nThe initial contagion in the country was mainly connected with the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy]] as there are circa 70,000 residents<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comuni-italiani.it/statistiche/stranieri/mk.html|title=Macedoni in Italia|website=comuni-italiani.it|language=it}}</ref>  of [[Italy]] from [[North Macedonia]] and due to a mass hysteria about the virus itself there was a mass returning to [[North Macedonia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/dva-novi-potvrdeni-sluchai-na-korona-virus-vo-debar/|title=\u0414\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440|date=6 March 2020|website=zdravstvo.gov.mk|language=mk-MK|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n===February 2020===\nOn '''26 February''', [[North Macedonia]] confirmed its first case of SARS-CoV-2, a 50-year-old woman that got tested at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases in [[Skopje]]. She had been in [[Italy]] for a month and was sick for two weeks. Upon returning to North Macedonia, she immediately reported herself to the clinic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/prv-sluchaj-na-zabolen-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=2020-02-26|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/china-coronavirus-outbreak-latest-updates-200226003835539.html|title=First case of coronavirus confirmed in North Macedonia|date=26 February 2020|publisher=Al Jazeera|url-status=live|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> This case was isolated and didn't lead to further infections.\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\n===March 2020===\nOn '''6 March''', two more cases were confirmed positive: a married couple from [[Balanci]], [[Centar \u017dupa]], who were residents of [[Brescia]], [[Italy]], and presumably returned to the country out of fear of the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sitel.com.mk/dva-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-0|title=\u0414\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=6 March 2020|website=Sitel|language=mk|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> They entered North Macedonia on 27 February and went to the clinic in [[Debar]] on 2 March. They were not initially tested for SARS-CoV-2, but when their symptoms were getting worse they were tested on 6 March. After getting positive results, the couple was transferred to the Clinic in Skopje to be taken care of.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.giornaledibrescia.it/brescia-e-hinterland/da-brescia-alla-macedonia-due-positivi-al-coronavirus-1.3465324/|title=Da Brescia alla Macedonia, due positivi al coronavirus|date=7 March 2020|website=Giornale di Brescia|language=it|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''9 March''' the number of infected people in the country increased to 7 - three family members of the cases registered on 6 of March and Nina Caca Biljanovska, the director of the Clinic for Skin Diseases in Skopje. Biljanovska's case caused controversy, as she did not self-isolate after returning from a vacation in Italy. Moreover, she had continued going to work and was a speaker at a conference attended by 100 people before getting tested. The Minister of health subsequently fired her.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%d0%b2%d0%ba%d1%83%d0%bf%d0%bd%d0%be-%d1%81%d0%b5%d0%b4%d1%83%d0%bc%d0%bc%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%b7%d0%b0%d1%80%d0%b0%d0%b7%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%be%d0%b4-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%be%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%b2/|title=\u0412\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e \u0441\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043c\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0441\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0458\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0443\u0436\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043e\u0434 \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440|last=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=9 March 2020|website=\u041c\u0410\u041a\u0424\u0410\u041a\u0421|language=mk-MK|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%D1%84%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%BF%D1%87%D0%B5-%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B0-%D0%B7%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D1%81%D0%BE-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80/|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u0414\u0438\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u045c\u0435 \u0431\u0438\u0434\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430|date=10 March 2020|publisher=Makfax|url-status=live|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''10 March''', after a formal request from the mayor of [[Debar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/sovetot-na-debar-bara-iten-prekin-na-nastavata-vo-uchilishtata-poradi-koronavirusot/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u0431\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0438\u0442\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0438\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442|date=10 March 2020|website=Telma|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> (the city where 5 of the 7 cases were found)  and the controversies regarding Biljanovska the Ministry of Health of North Macedonia implemented stronger measures to prevent further spreading of the virus, including a temporary two week closure of all education institutes (from kindergartens to universities), prohibition of traveling to the most infected countries ([[China]], [[Korea]], Italy, [[France]], [[Germany]], etc.), prohibition of all public events and closure of sport events to the public.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/vonredni-merki-na-vladata-protiv-korona-virusot/?__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=b51217bf8577b4a88a9e253e58ed1549698a59bb-1583919165-0-AYI8DAACqOSWx00wOsG9XHQJ6T-3Ij5mCw1_NyCmHJqry57wZy6H91IU7fSJACpVP-jrwKDVzyiF1Tt3vxapMcyM9wf70QUZ9heDY2lq5hbDyPf0Je1DWcxSD5WoFDWhQJu1wiPT_ot30lue_-WSFLX67PiFSJRIHoRL5VCW7O776sBBbU35c_GV8zfR8nJ07uiynPY2A85FYiyMq3YzVNi1R2-xN6JGMXifXD5ZL0uOe-VyWPSBHicd8DI4TYhSI5p_44h_3fe78aEhqN_zbJOzBQwv1BRRiaSuD6gRcyijmuHLxXibBkzytCyKdpmzHqrMeOPT4csXMV6E2LxI76E|title=\u0412\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442|date=10 March 2020|website=Telma|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> Later that day the first case was confirmed to tested negatively on the repeated coronavirus test. The patient, however, is still recovering in the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novamakedonija.com.mk/featured/%D0%B2%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%BE%D1%82-%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%81%D1%82-%D0%B7%D0%B0-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B2%D0%BE%D0%B7%D0%B0/|title=\u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u0435 \u043d\u0435\u0433\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0435\u043d|date=10 March 2020|website=NovaMakedonija|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> \n\n[[File:SARS-Covid2 Quarantined areas in North Macedonia.png|thumb|Quarantined areas on 13 March in red]]\n\nOn '''11 March''' two more cases were confirmed positive, both from Debar<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/dvajca-novi-zaboleni-od-koronavirus/|title=\u0414\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441|date=11 March 2020|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|language=mk|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> They are related to the first cases registered in the town.\n\nOn '''13 March''' four more cases were confirmed positive. As all 4 were from Debar, the Government declared a [[state of emergency]] in the municipalities of Debar and  Centar \u017dupa. All movement inside and outside the two quarantined municipalities was banned; only people living there were allowed to return to their homes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.mk/a/30486178.html|title=\u041a\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u0438 \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440 \u0416\u0443\u043f\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442, \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0437\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435|date=13 March 2020|website=slobodnaevropa.mk|language=mk-MK|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Later on, President Pendarovski made a decision on the engagement of the Army in affected areas in Debar and Centar \u017dupa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%bf%d1%80%d0%b5%d1%82%d1%81%d0%b5%d0%b4%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b5%d0%bb%d0%be%d1%82-%d0%bf%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b4%d0%b0%d1%80%d0%be%d0%b2%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d0%b4%d0%be%d0%bd%d0%b5%d1%81%d0%b5-%d0%be%d0%b4/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0435 \u041e\u0434\u043b\u0443\u043a\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0430\u043d\u0433\u0430\u0436\u0438\u0440\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0410\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u0438 \u0426\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440 \u0416\u0443\u043f\u0430|date=13 March 2020|website=alsat-m.tv|language=mk-MK|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Also it was announced that entries of foreign nationals to the country arriving from 'high-risk countries' would start getting denied.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-heath-coronavirus-northmacedonia/north-macedonia-bars-foreigners-arriving-from-high-risk-countries-over-coronavirus-idUSKBN2101NI?fbclid=IwAR0K-J4_hgAb5COQ6LxvQyV6kro6gdjpnZFgEinZ_L96HXJZsaKaavBz1UY|title=North Macedonia bars foreigners arriving from 'high-risk countries' over coronavirus|publisher=[[Reuters]]|date=13 March 2020|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''14 March''', 8 people were tested for coronavirus, 6 of which returned positive (5 from Debar and one from Skopje returning from a trip to [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]). A total of 14 of the patients were hospitalized at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases in Skopje, while the 5 new cases from Debar remained in the local hospital.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 \u0448\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 18 |url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%d0%b2%d0%b8%d0%b4%d0%b5%d0%be-%d1%83%d1%88%d1%82%d0%b5-%d1%88%d0%b5%d1%81%d1%82-%d0%bb%d0%b8%d1%86%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%be/ |website=Makfax |accessdate=14 March 2020 |language=mk |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''16 March''', 7 persons (5 officially) were positive (4 from Debar, 1 from Skopje and two tested in a private clinic). The patient in [[Skopje]] had just returned from a trip to the [[Netherlands]] via [[Vienna]], the two additional cases tested positive in the private [[Filip II Hospital, Skopje|\u017dan Mitrev Hospital]]. They got retested by the public laboratory the following day and their positive results got confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0414\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 7 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430, \u0442\u0440\u043e\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435! |url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%b4%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b5%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b0-%d0%b2%d0%ba%d1%83%d0%bf%d0%bd%d0%be-7-%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%bd%d0%b8/ |website=Alsat-m |accessdate=16 March 2020 |language=mk |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Because of the increased number of cases, both domestically and globally, the Government of North Macedonia decided to close the two international airports (Skopje and Ohrid) and ban foreigners from entering the country. The ban does not affect diplomats and medical personnel (which are required to obtain permission from the Ministry of Interior) and truck drivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nezavisen.mk/se-zatvoraat-megjunarodniot-aerodrom-skopje-i-site-kopneni-granichni-premini/|title=\u0421\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0430\u0430\u0442 \u041c\u0435\u0453\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0430\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0440\u043e\u043c \"\u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435\" \u0438 \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043f\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438|publisher=nezavisen.mk|date=16 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''17 March''' 5 new positive cases were confirmed - 4 in Debar (two nurses and two doctors, one of whom was Arben Agolli, former mayoral candidate and political activist<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://republika.mk/vesti/makedonija/personalot-pozitiven-na-korona-ambulantata-vo-debar-pod-karantin/ |title = \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0435\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430, \u0430\u043c\u0431\u0443\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0414\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0440 \u043f\u043e\u0434 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d - \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430}}</ref>) and one in Skopje, raising the number to 32.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/ushte-pet-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=Telma|date=17 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref> Political leaders decided to postpone the early parliamentary elections scheduled for 12 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mk.voanews.com/a/5332708.html|title=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043b\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u045c\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u043e\u0434\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0430\u0442|publisher=VOA News|date=17 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''18 March''', 4 new cases were confirmed positive, all of them Macedonian citizens from Skopje coming from [[Belgium]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://centar.mk/blog/2020/03/18/novi-chetiri-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-zemjava-site-se-od-skopje/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430, \u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435|publisher=Centar.mk|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> [[Prime Minister of North Macedonia|Prime Minister]] [[Oliver Spasovski]] announced that the Government is considering declaring a State of Emergency in the country, something that had never happened before.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kanal5.com.mk/vladata-pobara-voveduvanje-vonredna-sostojba-vo-celata-drzhava/a413682|title=\u0412\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0432\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0446\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0434\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u0430|publisher=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b 5|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> The State of Emergency was officially declared by the President later the same day and following this event, since the Parliament was dismissed, the Government gained legislative and executive power.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nezavisen.mk/pendarovski-proglasi-vonredna-sostojba/|title=\u041f\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0438 \u0432\u043e\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430|publisher=Nezavisen|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> Later that day 7 more people were tested positive on the virus (4 in Skopje and 3 in Debar).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sitel.com.mk/ushte-7-pozitivni-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-brojot-na-bolni-se-iskachi-na-42|title=\u0423\u0448\u0442\u0435 7 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0447\u0438 \u043d\u0430 42|publisher=\u0421\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b|date=18 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''19 March''', 6 new cases were confirmed positive: 3 in Debar, 1 in Skopje, 1 in [[Gostivar]], and 1 in [[\u0160tip]]. The case from Gostivar is a Macedonian citizen coming from [[Switzerland]], the case from \u0160tip is a 4-year-old that got infected at a kindergarten in [[England]] and the rest are domestic citizens related to previously confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kanal5.com.mk/mz-do-16-chasot-shest-novi-sluchai-so-koronavirus-megju-niv-i-chetirigodishno-devojche-zarazeno-vo-gradinka-vo-anglija/a413930|title=\u041c\u0417: \u0414\u043e 16 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0442 \u0448\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u043c\u0435\u0453\u0443 \u043d\u0438\u0432 \u0438 \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u043d\u043e \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0458\u0447\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u043e \u0432\u043e \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0410\u043d\u0433\u043b\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b 5|date=19 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''20 March''', 19 new cases, all of them in Skopje, were confirmed positive. 17 of them were tested at the private [[Filip II Hospital, Skopje|\u017dan Mitrev Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://press24.mk/mz-19-novozaboleni-od-koronavirus-brojkata-na-dijagnosticirani-pacienti-vo-zemjata-e-67-lica|title=\u041c\u0417: 19 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 - \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0435 67 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=press24.mk|date=20 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> With this outbreak Skopje surpassed Debar in number of confirmed cases. Later the same day 3 people tested positive (2 in Skopje and 1 in \u0160tip). One of the people from Skopje said that she had travelled to [[Serbia]] before she was confirmed positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv21.tv/mk/novi-tri-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-sega-brojkata-e-70/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0435 70|publisher=TV 21|date=20 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> Again, later the same day 6 new cases tested positive (4 in Skopje and a married couple in [[Kavadarci]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kanal5.com.mk/shest-novozaboleni-lica-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija-vkupno-76-lica-do-21-00-chasot/a414184|title=\u0428\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430,\u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 76 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0434\u043e 21.00 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0442|publisher=\u041a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b 5|date=20 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''21 March''', 9 new cases were confirmed positive: 7 in Skopje and 2 in \u0160tip.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82-%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B8-%D1%81%D0%BB%D1%83%D1%87%D0%B0%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81-%D0%B2%D0%BE-%D0%B7%D0%B5/|title=\u0414\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u2013 \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 85 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438|publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=21 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> Later the same day the Government imposed a [[curfew]] as a protection measure against the virus outbreak. The curfew will be in the place everyday starting 22 March from 9 p.m. to 6 a.m.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ako.mk/%d0%be%d0%b4-%d1%83%d1%82%d1%80%d0%b5-%d1%81%d0%b5-%d0%b2%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b5%d0%b4%d1%83%d0%b2%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%bb%d0%b8%d1%86%d0%b8%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8-%d1%87%d0%b0%d1%81-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%bc%d0%b0/|title=\u041e\u0434 \u0443\u0442\u0440\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u0432\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0447\u0430\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043e\u0434 21 \u0434\u043e 6 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0442|publisher=\u0410\u043a\u043e.\u043c\u043a|date=21 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''22 March''', 29 new cases were confirmed positive: 22 in Skopje, 3 in \u0160tip, 2 in Debar, 1 in [[Ohrid]], and 1 in Kumanovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/brojkata-na-zaboleni-od-koronavirus-vo-zemjava-dostigna-114-lica/|title=\u0411\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 114|publisher=A1on|date=22 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref> On 22 March, North Macedonia recorded the first fatality, \u0430 57-year-old woman from [[Kumanovo]] that was confirmed positive to the virus [[postmortem]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vecer.mk/node/484671|title=\u041f\u0420\u0412 \u0421\u041c\u0420\u0422\u0415\u041d \u0421\u041b\u0423\u0427\u0410\u0408 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=\u0412\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0440|date=22 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''23 March''', 22 new cases were confirmed positive: 15 in Skopje, 4 in Debar, 2 Kumanovo, and 1 in Ohrid.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://republika.mk/vesti/makedonija/potvrdeni-ushte-22-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vkupnata-brojka-sega-e-136/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0443\u0448\u0442\u0435 22 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u0435 136|publisher=\u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430|date=23 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> The same day the second death was confirmed, a 63-year-old man from Debar that was hospitalized in Skopje on 17 March, reportedly his situation was stable and he suddenly got in a bad state in the night when he was attached to a respiratory machine but that wasn't enough.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%D0%B2%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80-%D1%81%D0%BC%D1%80%D1%82%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D1%81%D0%BB%D1%83%D1%87%D0%B0%D1%98-%D0%BE%D0%B4-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81-%D0%B2%D0%BE-%D0%BC/|title=\u0412\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0441\u043c\u0440\u0442\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=23 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''24 March''', 12 new cases were confirmed positive: 7 in Skopje and 5 in Kumanovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mkd.mk/makedonija/obrazovanie-i-zdravstvo/12-novi-zarazeni-od-koronavirus-vkupniot-broj-dostigna-148-lica|title=12 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 148 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=\u041c\u041a\u0414.\u043c\u043a|date=24 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''25 March''', 29 new cases were confirmed positive: 20 in Skopje and 3 in Kumanovo, 3 in [[Veles, North Macedonia|Veles]], 2 in [[Prilep]], and 1 in Debar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telma.com.mk/29-novi-sluchai-na-zarazeni-od-koronaviruv-vkupno-177-zaboleni/|title=29 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0432, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 177 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438|publisher=\u0422\u0435\u043b\u043c\u0430|date=25 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref> The same day the \"Patient zero\" of the outbreak in [[Debar]], the wife of the couple from Balanci that tested positive on 6 March was confirmed as the third death case. She was 66 years old. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.mk/a/30509237.html|title=\u0422\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u0436\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442, \u0434\u043e\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0443\u0432\u0430\u045a\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u043a\u0435\u043d\u0434|publisher=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0421\u043b\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0430|date=25 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''26 March''', 24 new cases were registered positive: 15 from Skopje, 4 from Kumanovo, 2 from Debar, and 1 from Ohrid and \u0160tip each, as well as the first case from Tetovo. 2 patients recovered.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://360stepeni.mk/novi-24-zarazeni-so-kornavirus-vkupnata-brojka-vo-zemjava-iznesuva-201-litse/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 24 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 201 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0435|publisher=360 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438|date=26 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''27 March''', 18 new cases were registered positive: 11 from Skopje, 4 from Prilep, 2 from Kumanovo, and 1 from Tetovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://360stepeni.mk/filipche-brojkata-na-zaboleni-od-kornoavirus-shto-ja-spodeluvame-e-tselosno-tochna-vo-momentov-iznesuva-219/|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u0411\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0448\u0442\u043e \u0458\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u0435 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0441\u043d\u043e \u0442\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u2013 \u0432\u043e \u043c\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 219|publisher=360 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438|date=27 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''28 March''', 22 new cases were confirmed positive: 9 in Skopje, 3 in Kumanovo and Struga each; 2 in Tetovo, Prilep, and Debar each; and 1 in Bitola. Also it was confirmed the fourth death case, a 66 years old woman from Struga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/registrirani-22-novi-sluchai-na-koronavirus-vo-zemjata-pochina-edna-zhena-od-okolinata-na-struga/|title=\u041f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0421\u0442\u0440\u0443\u0448\u043a\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, 22 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0442\u0430|publisher=A1on|date=28 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> \n\nOn '''29 March''', 18 new cases were confirmed positive: 6 in \u0160tip, 3 in Skopje, 3 in Veles, 2 in Struga, 1 in Strumica, 1 in Debar, 1 in Tetovo, and 1 in [[Gevgelija]]. Also two new death cases, a 31-year-old and 91-year-old men were confirmed today.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/%d0%b2%d0%ba%d1%83%d0%bf%d0%bd%d0%be-257-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%80%d0%be%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%b2%d0%b8%d1%80%d1%83%d1%81-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%bc%d0%b0%d0%ba%d0%b5/|title=\u0412\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 259 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430, \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0430 6 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=29 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''30 March''', 26 new cases were confirmed positive: 19 in Skopje, 3 in Kumanovo, 1 in Prilep, 1 in Tetovo, 1 in Debar, and 1 in [[Kriva Palanka]]. The seventh death was recorded, a 79 years old man from Debar, while 9 patients recovered (8 from Skopje and 1 from Debar).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sdk.mk/index.php/makedonija/osum-meditsinski-litsa-i-dvajtsa-patsienti-se-pozitivni-na-koronavirus-od-skopskiot-zavod-za-rehabilitatsija/|title=\u041e\u0441\u0443\u043c \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043e\u0434 \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434 \u0437\u0430 \u0440\u0435\u0445\u0430\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430|publisher=sdk.mk|date=30 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''31 March''' the Ministry of Health announced 44 new cases: 23 in Kumanovo, 11 in Skopje, 5 in Tetovo, 2 in Prilep, 2 in Struga, and 1 in Prilep. A 45-year-old man from Kumanovo and a 78-year-old man from Debar, both with pre-existing conditions, passed away. Up to that day 3,518 tests were made.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/registrirani-44-novi-sluchai-vkupnata-brojka-na-dijagnosticirani-iznesuva-329-lica-na-klinikata-za-infektivni-bolesti-i-febrilni-sostojbi-pochinaa-2-lica/|title=\u0420\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 44 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438-\u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 329 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430, \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0438 \u0444\u0435\u0431\u0440\u0438\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0430 2 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=zdravstvo.gov.mk|date=31 March 2020|language=mk|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===April 2020===\nOn '''1 April''' the Ministry of Health announced 25 new positive cases: 7 in Kumanovo, 7 in Skopje, 4 in Tetovo, 3 in [[Bitola]], 2 in Struga, 1 in Gevgelija and 1 in Ko\u010dani. A 64-years-old woman from Struga with pre-existing conditions, passed away. It was also discovered that a 66-years-old woman, also from Struga, who had died a day before tested positive on the post mortem test. 5 patients recovered as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/potvrdeni-25-novi-sluchai-pozitivni-na-pozitivni-na-kovid-19-vkupnata-brojka-na-dijagnosticirani-iznesuva-354-na-infektivnata-klinika-vo-skopje-pochina-pacientka-od-labunishta/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 25 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434 19-\u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0438\u0458\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430 354, \u043d\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043a\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u041b\u0430\u0431\u0443\u043d\u0438\u0448\u0442\u0430|publisher=zdravstvo.gov.mk|date=1 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://iph.mk/covid19-31-3-2020/|title=\u0421\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0441\u043e covid-19 \u0432\u043e \u0440\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u2013 31.03.2020|publisher=iph.mk|date=1 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''2 April''', 30 new cases were registered positive: 12 from Skopje, 9 from Prilep, 8 from Kumanovo, and 1 from Kriva Palanka.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tera.mk/%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-30-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%b4%d1%80%d0%b6%d0%b0%d0%b2%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b0-%d0%be%d0%b4-%d0%bd%d0%b8%d0%b2-9-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%bf%d1%80%d0%b8%d0%bb/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 30 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0432\u043e \u0434\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430, \u043e\u0434 \u043d\u0438\u0432 9 \u0432\u043e \u041f\u0440\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043f|publisher=\u0422\u0435\u0440\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0437\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=2 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''3 April''', 46 new cases were registered positive: 23 from Kumanovo, 13 from Skopje, 2 from Debar, 2 from Veles, 2 from Gevgelija, 2 from Tetovo, 1 from Prilep and 1 from Gostivar. One more death was also confirmed: a 68-years-old man from the villages around Tetovo. In the evening, another suspected fatality was confirmed to be positive for Covid-19, a 70-years-old man from Kumanovo. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libertas.mk/pochinatiot-paczient-od-kumanovo-na-infektivnata-klinika-vo-skop%d1%98e-pozitiven-na-kovid-19/?__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=c8a88d72c45f43925ac6624a1936112617beb2ca-1585944904-0-AT5POI2mwfEY3A7x0TPkrvr7dVuTJZE_91hUdMjd5Ylcc6Eoq0kAJ6n5O7YDLAjObwKDZ15VbTBV2ssYWh2HntrapMBiWQNzrN8KZbmyzmLPFz3WYqeUSSHM4Ne-X5GshNLqzZWhdjzskkchrr5TRbaxCt8Z6eaDJm9tVYAcqo6FUGeH8Tta4CbJDfEHvkXWuIonLU-fwDoHoOFlSMDK3mG62ejVdVNT1Za_yjiJ3zHLToDaDV-ZPOnV5f1YzgMU_-XLANAfdmInqbtsegG4a3OEZCbhOer4MERO1f5j9VCrmLVsvE_oFryFKPbDu9mOtJ1ikRLdx173_bWbGu4_I3DOqjdlkw3ZtsAkS-ew3gHjGUR0nTe1nFCxDaqM1CYLL46UW-rHq5ZQte6RZlf_D6I|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u0443\u043c\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0418\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432\u043e \u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0435 - \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0435\u043d \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-199|publisher=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0422\u0412|date=3 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''4 April''', 53 new cases were registered positive: 14 from [[Struga]], 13 from Skopje, 8 from Kumanovo, 6 from [[Ko\u010dani]], 5 from \u0160tip, 2 from Prilep, Tetovo and Gostivar each and 1 from Veles. Also five new death cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/5-%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b8-%d0%b8-53-%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-%d1%81%d0%bb%d1%83%d1%87%d0%b0%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8%d0%b4-19-%d0%b2%d0%be-%d0%b7%d0%b5/|title=5 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438 \u0438 53 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-19 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430|publisher=\u0410\u043b\u0441\u0430\u0442-\u041c|date=4 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''5 April''', 72 new cases were registered positive: 21 from Kumanovo, 14 from Skopje, 11 from Tetovo, 9 from Prilep, 7 from Ko\u010dani, 2 from Kru\u0161evo, Bitola and Radovi\u0161 each, 1 from Struga, Veles, Gostivar and \u0160tip each. Also one new case was confirmed dead, a 63-year-old man from Struga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://opserver.mk/makedonija/novi-72-sluchaja-pozitivni-na-koronavirus-eden-pochinat-dosega-vkupno-555-zaboleni/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=novi-72-sluchaja-pozitivni-na-koronavirus-eden-pochinat-dosega-vkupno-555-zaboleni|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 72 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442, \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0433\u0430 \u0432\u043a\u0443\u043f\u043d\u043e 555 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438 |publisher=\u041e\u043f\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0435\u0440 |date=5 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Later the same day the Institute of Public Health of the Republic of North Macedonia corrected the previously announced numbers by cities in term that one case from Gostivar is a citizen returning from Slovenia quarantined in Gostivar but lives in Strumica and one case from Tetovo is a citizen returning from abroad who is quarantined in Tetovo but lives in Radovi\u0161.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://makpress.mk/Home/PostDetails?PostId=339670|title=\u0418\u0408\u0417 \u0441\u043e \u043a\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0432\u043e \u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043e \u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0440 \u0441\u0435 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0435\u045a\u0435 |publisher=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0441 |date=5 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''6 April''', 15 new cases were registered positive: 8 in Kumanovo, 4 in Skopje and 1 in Tetovo, Struga and \u0160tip each. Also it was confirmed three new death cases: a 69-year-old and 65-years-old men from Tetovo and a 40-year-old man from Ko\u010dani. 6 patients recovered as well. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://kurir.mk/makedonija/vesti/raste-brojot-na-zrtvi-i-zarazeni-vo-makedonija-koronavirus-imaat-570-lica/|title=\u0420\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0435 \u0431\u0440\u043e\u0458\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0438 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438: \u0412\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u0430\u0442 570 \u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430|publisher=\u041a\u0443\u0440\u0438\u0440|date=6 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''7 April,''' 29 new cases were registered positive: 15 in Skopje, 7 in Kumanovo, 3 in Struga and Ko\u010dani each and 1 in Prilep. It was also confirmed 5 new deaths: a 52 and 53-years-old men from Kumanovo, an 81-year-old woman from \u0160tip,  a 65-year-old woman from Struga and a 62-year-old woman from Tetovo. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kajgana.com/novi-29-zarazeni-i-5-smrtni-sluchai-od-covid-19|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 29 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0438 5 \u0441\u043c\u0440\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043e\u0434 COVID-19|date=2020-04-07|website=\u041a\u0430\u0458\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> Later that day, it was confirmed one more death. A 45-year-old man from Skopje heading towards the City General hospital \"8th September\" for treatment. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.kajgana.com/pochina-45-godishen-skopjanec-zarazen-od-koronavirus-na-pat-kon-bolnicata-8-septemvri|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 45-\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0458\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0446 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u043d \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430\u0442\u0430 \"8 \u0421\u0435\u043f\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0432\u0440\u0438\"|date=2020-04-07|website=\u041a\u0430\u0458\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nOn '''8 April''', 18 new cases were registered positive: 7 in Skopje, 4 in Prilep, 2 in Bitola and Kumanovo each, 1 in Kru\u0161evo, Ko\u010dani and Kavadarci. Two new deaths were also confirmed, a 73-year-old man from Kumanovo, and the one positive case from Kavadarci. He was a 44 year old foreign citizen found dead in his apartment, who was tested postmortem. 7 patients recovered as well. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zdravstvo.gov.mk/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/info-covid-19-do-7-april.pdf|title=\u0421\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0458\u0431\u0430 \u0441\u043e covid-19 \u0432\u043e \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 \u2013 07.04.2020|date=2020-04-08|website=zdravstvo|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Later that same day, one more death was confirmed. A 27-year-old woman from Kumanovo which, while infected, gave birth on the 30th of March. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kajgana.com/pochina-rodilkata-od-kumanovo-pozitivna-na-covid-19|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043b\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u0443\u043c\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 COVID-19|date=2020-04-08|website=\u041a\u0430\u0458\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0430|language=mk|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nOn '''9 April''', 46 new cases were registered positive: 13 in Kumanovo, 12 in Skopje, 8 in Prilep and Veles each, 2 in Struga and 1 in Tetovo, Ko\u010dani and Probi\u0161tip each. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%b0%d1%86%d0%b8%d0%b5%d0%bd%d1%82-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b5%d0%bd-%d0%bd%d0%b0-%d0%ba%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8%d0%b4-19-%d1%80%d0%b5/|title=\u0420\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 46 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-19|publisher=\u0410\u043b\u0441\u0430\u0442-\u041c|date=9 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''10 April''', 48 new cases were registered positive: 25 in Kumanovo, 11 in Skopje, 4 in Prilep, 3 in Struga, 2 in Gostivar and 1 in Ohrid, \u0160tip, and Tetovo each. Two new deaths were also confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alsat-m.tv/mk/%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%b0-%d0%b4%d0%b2%d0%b0%d1%98%d1%86%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%b0%d1%86%d0%b8%d0%b5%d0%bd%d1%82%d0%b8-%d0%bf%d0%be%d0%b7%d0%b8%d1%82%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%bd%d0%b0-2/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0430 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434-19|publisher=\u0410\u043b\u0441\u0430\u0442-\u041c|date=10 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn '''11 April''', 49 new cases were registered positive: 14 in Kumanovo, 13 in Skopje, 8 in Prilep, 6 in \u0160tip and Veles each and 1 in Gostivar and Ko\u010dani each. Two new deaths were also confirmed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://puls24.mk/%d0%bd%d0%be%d0%b2%d0%b8-49-%d0%b7%d0%b0%d1%80%d0%b0%d0%b7%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%b8-%d0%b8-%d0%b4%d0%b2%d0%b0%d1%98%d1%86%d0%b0-%d0%bf%d0%be%d1%87%d0%b8%d0%bd%d0%b0%d1%82%d0%b8-%d0%be%d0%b4-%d0%ba%d0%be/|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438 49 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0458\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0438 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u041e\u0420\u041e\u041d\u0410\u0412\u0418\u0420\u0423\u0421\u041e\u0422 \u0432\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 24 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0430.|publisher=\u041f\u0443\u043b\u0441 24|date=11 April 2020|language=mk|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Prevention measures ==\nPreparatory measures against a potential outbreak started in late January 2020. National measures against the pandemic are led by health minister [[Venko Filip\u010de]] and the Commission for Infectious Diseases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sdk.mk/index.php/makedonija/podgotveni-sme-za-koronavirusot-nema-potreba-od-panika-veli-ministerot-za-zdravstvo-filipche/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0434\u0433\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043c\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442, \u043d\u0435\u043c\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430, \u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435|publisher=SDK |date=31 January 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nStarting from 27 January, thermal cameras installed at the [[Skopje Airport]], started monitoring passengers coming from [[Istanbul]] and [[Dubai]] who serve as links to [[China]], which was at the moment the epicenter of the epidemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.mk/a/30397586.html|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u0411\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430, \u0430\u043c\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u0443\u0442\u0440\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u0442 |publisher=slobodnaevropa.mk |date=26 January 2020|language=mk|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Following the first meeting with [[WHO]] representative Jihane Tawilah, the country's preparedness for early detection & stopping the spread of the virus was assessed as satisfactory. Health minister Venko Filip\u010de announced that North Macedonia's healthcare system is completely prepared for a potential outbreak. In addition to the thermal cameras, information leaflets were distributed to police stations and the custom checks at all border passes.\n\nOn 4 February, the first reagents to detect the virus were imported from [[Ni\u0161]], [[Serbia]]. Filip\u010de said that at the moment the country had about 40.000 surgical masks and medical protective suits, but additional procurement was considered to prepare the country for a potential outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fokus.mk/filipche-ne-postoi-nitu-eden-somnitelen-sluchaj-za-korona-virus-vo-zemjava/|title=\u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f\u0447\u0435: \u041d\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438 \u043d\u0438\u0442\u0443 \u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u0437\u0435\u043c\u0458\u0430\u0432\u0430 |publisher=Fokus |date=4 February 2020|language=mk|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Worldwide Coronavirus Map] \u2013 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE)\n* [https://koronavirus.gov.mk/en/media-center Latest information on COVID-19 and measures for prevention of spreading issued by the Government] - Official information about the Coronavirus in North Macedonia.\n* [https://gdi-sk.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/2096bd4b051b42948ac3f5747e80c3a5 Status Map, North Macedonia] - GIS Map of all cases North Macedonia.\n\n{{Portal bar|Medicine|Europe|North Macedonia}}\n\n{{2019-nCoV|state=expanded}}\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "name_user": "Atlonche", "label": "safe", "comment": "update for April 11th", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_North_Macedonia"}
{"title_page": "Harpo Marx", "text_new": "{{short description|American comedian}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Harpo Marx\n| image        = Harpo_Marx_1948.jpg\n| imagesize    = 200px\n| caption      = Harpo Marx in 1948\n| birth_name   = Adolph Marx\n| birth_date   = {{birth date|1888|11|23}}\n| birth_place = [[Manhattan]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| death_date   = {{death date and age|1964|09|28|1888|11|23}}\n| death_place  = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation   = {{hlist|Comedian|actor|mime artist|musician}}\n| years_active = 1910\u20131963\n| height       = 5 ft 5 1/2 in (1.66 m)\n| parents      = {{ubl|[[Sam Marx|Sam \"Frenchie\" Marx]]|[[Minnie Marx|Minnie Sch\u00f6nberg]]}}\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Susan Fleming]]|1936<!--As marriage ended with his death, year is omitted per Template:Marriage instructions--->}} \n| children     = 4 \n| relatives    = {{ubl|[[Groucho Marx]] (brother)|[[Chico Marx]] (brother)|[[Gummo Marx]] (brother)|[[Zeppo Marx]] (brother)|[[Al Shean]] (maternal uncle)}}\n}}\n\n'''Arthur''' \"'''Harpo'''\" '''Marx''' (born '''Adolph Marx'''; November 23, 1888 \u2013 September 28, 1964) was an American [[comedian]], actor, [[mime artist]], and musician, and the second-oldest of the [[Marx Brothers]]. In contrast to the mainly verbal comedy of his brothers [[Groucho Marx]] and [[Chico Marx]], Harpo's comic style was visual, being an example of both [[clown]] and [[pantomime]] traditions. He wore a curly reddish blonde wig, and never spoke during performances (he blew a horn or [[Whistling|whistled]] to communicate). He frequently used [[Theatrical property|props]] such as a horn cane, made up of a pipe, tape, and a bulbhorn, and he played the [[harp]] in most of his films.<ref name=\"birth\">{{cite web| title=Harpo Marx| website=Biography| url=https://www.biography.com/people/harpo-marx-16242175|date=April 2, 2014| accessdate=4 August 2018}}{{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nHarpo was born on November 23, 1888, in [[Manhattan]]. He grew up in a neighborhood now known as [[Carnegie Hill]] on the [[Upper East Side]] of Manhattan, on East 93rd Street off [[Lexington Avenue]]. The turn-of-the-century tenement that Harpo later called (in his autobiography ''Harpo Speaks!'') \"the first real home I can remember\" was populated with European immigrants, mostly artisans\u2014which even included a glass blower. Just across the street were the oldest [[brownstone]]s in the area, owned by people like [[David L. Loew]] and William Orth.\n\nHarpo's parents were [[Sam Marx]] (called \"Frenchie\" throughout his life) and his wife, [[Minnie Marx|Minnie Schoenberg Marx]]. Minnie's brother was [[Al Shean]]. Marx's family was Jewish. His mother was from [[East Frisia]] in Germany, and his father was a native of Alsace in [[France]] and worked as a tailor.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://judaisme.sdv.fr/perso/marxbr/geneal.htm| title=La famille paternelle des Marx Brothers| website=Judaisme.sdv.fr| language=French| trans-title=The Paternal Family of the Marx Brothers| quote=Extract from the Review of the Circle of Jewish Geneology| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title=Mrs. Minnie Marx. Mother of Four Marx Brothers, Musical Comedy Stars, Dies| newspaper=[[The New York Times]]| url=http://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1929/09/16/95997162.html?pageNumber=21| date=September 16, 1929| page=21| accessdate=2016-08-09| url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nHarpo received little formal education and left grade school at age eight (mainly due to bullying)<ref name=\"speaks\"/> during his second attempt to pass the second grade. He began to work, gaining employment in numerous odd jobs alongside his brother [[Chico Marx|Chico]] to contribute to the family income, including selling newspapers, working in a butcher shop, and as an errand office boy.<ref>Marx 1961, pp. 17\u201319</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===On stage===\nIn January 1910, Harpo joined two of his brothers, [[Groucho Marx|Julius]] (later \"Groucho\") and [[Gummo Marx|Milton]] (later \"Gummo\"), to form \"The Three Nightingales\", later changed to simply \"The Marx Brothers\". Multiple stories\u2014most unsubstantiated\u2014exist to explain Harpo's evolution as the \"silent\" character in the brothers' act. In his memoir, Groucho wrote that Harpo simply wasn't very good at memorizing dialogue, and thus was ideal for the role of the \"dunce who couldn't speak\", a common character in vaudeville acts of the time.<ref>Marx, Groucho (1959). Groucho And Me. Da Capo Press. {{ISBN|978-0-306-80666-7}}, p. 46.</ref>\n\nHarpo gained his stage name during a card game at the Orpheum Theatre in [[Galesburg, Illinois]]. The dealer (Art Fisher) called him \"Harpo\" because he played the [[harp]].<ref name=\"speaks\">{{cite book| last=Marx| first=Harpo| author2=Rowland Barber| title=Harpo Speaks!| publisher=Limelight Editions| year=1988| location=New York| isbn=978-0879100360| url=https://archive.org/details/harpospeaks00marx}}</ref><ref name=\"Mitchell p169\">Mitchell 1996, p. 169</ref> He learned how to hold it properly from a picture of an angel playing a harp that he saw in a [[five-and-dime]]. No one in town knew how to play the harp, so Harpo tuned it as best he could, starting with one basic note and tuning it from there. Three years later he found out he had tuned it incorrectly, but he could not have tuned it properly; if he had, the strings would have broken each night. Harpo's method placed much less tension on the strings.{{citation needed|date=December 2011}} Although he played this way for the rest of his life, he did try to learn how to play correctly, and he spent considerable money hiring the best teachers. They spent their time listening to him, fascinated by the way he played.<ref name=\"speaks\"/> The major exception was [[Mildred Dilling]], a professional harpist who did teach Harpo the proper techniques of the instrument and collaborated with him regularly when he had difficulty with various compositions.<ref>{{cite news| title=Mildred Dilling, 88, a Harpist, Performed for 5 Presidents| url=https://www.nytimes.com/1983/01/03/obituaries/mildred-dilling-88-a-harpist-performed-for-5-presidents.html| accessdate=23 January 2018| newspaper=The New York Times| date=3 January 1983}}</ref>\n\nIn the autobiography ''Harpo Speaks!'' (1961), he recounts how [[Chico Marx|Chico]] found him jobs playing [[piano]] to accompany [[silent film|silent movies]]. Unlike Chico, Harpo could play only two songs on the piano, \"Waltz Me Around Again, Willie\" and \"Love Me and the World Is Mine,\" but he adapted this small repertoire in different tempos to suit the action on the screen. He was also seen playing a portion of Rachmaninoff's \"Prelude in C# minor\" in ''[[A Day at the Races (film)|A Day at the Races]]'' and chords on the piano in ''[[A Night at the Opera (film)|A Night at the Opera]]'', in such a way that the piano sounded much like a harp, as a prelude to actually playing the harp in that scene.\n\nHarpo had changed his name from Adolph to Arthur by 1911. This was due primarily to his dislike for the name Adolph (as a child, he was routinely called \"Ahdie\" instead). The name change may have also happened because of the similarity between Harpo's name and Adolph Marks, a prominent show business attorney in Chicago.<ref>{{cite book| last=Bader| first=Robert S.| title=Four of the Three Musketeers| publisher=Northwestern University Press| year=2016| location=Evanston, IL| page=147 |isbn=978-0-8101-3416-4}}</ref> [[Urban legends]] stating that the name change came about during [[World War I]] due to anti-German sentiment in the US, or during [[World War II]] because of the stigma that [[Adolf Hitler]] imposed on the name, are groundless.<ref>{{cite web| last=Mikkelson| first=Barbara and David| title=Lane Kibe| website=[[Snopes]]| date=2007-08-09| url=http://www.snopes.com/movies/actors/harpo.htm| accessdate=2008-01-01}}</ref>\n\n===On film===\n[[File:Harpo Marx playing the harp.jpeg|thumb|left|Harpo Marx playing the harp]]\nHis first screen appearance was in the film ''[[Humor Risk]]'' (1921), with his brothers, although according to Groucho, it was only screened once and then [[Lost film|lost]]. Four years later, Harpo appeared without his brothers in ''[[Too Many Kisses]]'' (1925), four years before the brothers' first released film, ''[[The Cocoanuts]]'' (1929). In ''Too Many Kisses'', Harpo spoke the only line he would ever speak on-camera in a movie: \"You sure you can't move?\"<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.marx-brothers.org/watching/film/Too_Many_Kisses.htm| title=Too Many Kisses (1925)| website=Marx-brothers.org| access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> (said to the film's tied-up hero before punching him). Fittingly, it was a silent movie, and the audience saw only his lips move and the line on a title card.\n\nHarpo was often cast as Chico's eccentric partner-in-crime, whom he would often help by playing charades to tell of Groucho's problem, and/or annoy by giving Chico his leg, either to give it a rest or as an alternative to a handshake.\n\n[[File:Marx Brothers 1931.jpg|thumb|From top: Chico, Harpo, Groucho, and Zeppo, ca. 1931]]\nHarpo became known for prop-laden [[Visual gag|sight gags]], in particular the seemingly [[Hammerspace|infinite number of odd things]] stored in his [[Overcoat|topcoat]]'s oversized pockets. In the film ''[[Horse Feathers]]'' (1932), Groucho, referring to an impossible situation, tells Harpo that he cannot \"burn the candle at both ends.\" Harpo immediately produces from within his coat pocket a lit candle burning at both ends. In the same film, a homeless man on the street asks Harpo for money for a cup of coffee, and he subsequently produces a steaming cup, complete with saucer, from inside his coat. Also in ''Horse Feathers'', he has a fish and a sword, and when he wants to go to his speakeasy, he stabs the fish in its mouth with his sword to give the password, \"Swordfish.\" In ''Duck Soup'', he produces a lit blowtorch to light a cigar. As author Joe Adamson put in his book, ''Groucho, Harpo, Chico and Sometimes Zeppo'', \"The president of the college has been shouted down by a mute.\"\n\nHarpo often used facial expressions and mime to get his point across. One of his facial expressions, which he used in every Marx Brothers film and stage play, beginning with ''Fun in Hi Skule'', was known as \"the Gookie.\" Harpo created it by mimicking the expression of Mr. Gehrke, a New York tobacconist who would make a similar face while concentrating on rolling cigars.<ref name=\"speaks\"/><ref name=\"Mitchell\">{{cite book| last=Mitchell| first=Glenn| title=The Marx Brothers Encyclopedia| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=e28dAQAAIAAJ&dq=the+marx+brothers+encyclopedia&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=gehrke| publisher=Reynolds & Hearn| year=2003| location=London| page=123| isbn=978-1903111499| url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nHarpo further distinguished his character by wearing a \"fright wig\". Early in his career it was dyed pink, as evidenced by color film posters of the time and by allusions to it in films, with character names such as \"Pinky\" in ''Duck Soup''. It tended to show as blonde on-screen due to the black-and-white film stock at the time. Over time, he darkened the pink to more of a reddish color, again films alluded to it with character names such as \"Rusty\".\n\nHis non-speaking in his early films was occasionally referred to by the other Marx Brothers, who were careful to imply that his character's not speaking was a choice rather than a disability. They would make joking reference to this part of his act. For example, in ''[[Animal Crackers (1930 film)|Animal Crackers]]'' his character was ironically dubbed \"The Professor\". In ''The Cocoanuts'', this exchange occurred:\n\n'''Groucho''': \"Who is this?\"\n\n'''Chico''': \"Dat's-a my partner, but he no speak.\"\n\n'''Groucho''': \"Oh, that's your [[wikt:silent partner|silent partner]]!\"\n\nIn later films, Harpo was repeatedly put in situations where he attempted to convey a vital message by whistling and pantomime, reinforcing the idea that his character was unable to speak.\n\nThe Marxes' film ''At the Circus (1939)'' contains a unique scene where Harpo is ostensibly heard saying \"A-choo!\" twice, as he sneezes. It is unclear, however, whether he actually voiced the line, or if he mimed it while someone said it off-camera.  \n\n===In other media===\n[[File:Harpo and Chico Marx General Electric Theater 1959.JPG|thumb|right|Harpo and Chico Marx in \"The Incredible Jewelry Robbery\" (1959)]]\n[[File:Harpo Marx Silent Panic DuPont Show 1960.JPG|thumb|right|Marx as the \"mechanical man\" in \"A Silent Panic\" (1960)]]\nIn 1933, following U.S. diplomatic recognition of the [[Soviet Union]], he spent six weeks in [[Moscow]] as a performer and goodwill ambassador.<ref name=\"speaks\" /> His tour was a huge success. Harpo's name was transliterated into Russian, using the Cyrillic alphabet, as \u0425\u0410\u0420\u041f\u041e \u041c\u0410\u0420\u041a\u0421, and was billed as such during his Soviet Union appearances. Harpo, having no knowledge of Russian, pronounced it as \"Exapno Mapcase\". At that time Harpo and the Soviet Foreign Minister [[Maxim Litvinov]] became friends and even performed a routine on stage together.<ref>''Current Biography 1941, pp 518\u201320.</ref> During this time he served as a secret courier; delivering communiques to and from the US embassy in Moscow at the request of Ambassador [[William Christian Bullitt, Jr.]], smuggling the messages in and out of Russia by taping a sealed envelope to his leg beneath his trousers, an event described in [[David Fromkin]]'s 1995 book ''In the Time of the Americans''.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=O1UNAAAAIBAJ&sjid=im4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=3199,8313638&dq=harpo-marx+soviet-union+courier \"At Our Best\"], ''[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]'', July 30, 1995. Accessed July 29, 2009.{{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref><ref>[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-26993299_ITM \"Was Harpo Marx The Silent Spy Who Stole Soviet Secrets?\"], ''Europe Intelligence Wire'', December 28, 2002. Accessed July 29, 2009.</ref> In ''Harpo Speaks!'', Marx describes his relief at making it out of the Soviet Union, recalling how \"I pulled up my pants, ripped off the tape, unwound the straps, handed over the dispatches from Ambassador Bullitt, and gave my leg its first scratch in ten days.\"<ref>Marx 1961, p. 336.</ref>\n\nThe Russia trip was later memorialized in a bizarre science fiction novella, ''The Foreign Hand Tie'' by [[Randall Garrett]], a tale of telepathic spies which is full of references to the Marx Brothers and their films.<ref>{{cite journal| first=Randall| last=Garrett| url=http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/30497| title=The Foreign Hand Tie| journal=[[Analog (magazine)|Analog]]| date=December 1961| via=[[Project Gutenberg]]| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> (The title itself is a Marx-like pun on the dual ideas of a \"foreign hand\" and a style of neckwear known as a \"[[four-in-hand knot|four-in-hand tie]].\")\n\nIn 1936, he was one of a number of performers and celebrities to appear as [[caricature]]s in the [[The Walt Disney Company|Walt Disney Production]] of ''[[Mickey's Polo Team]]''. Harpo was part of a team of [[polo]]-playing [[movie stars]] which included [[Charlie Chaplin]] and [[Laurel and Hardy]]. His mount was an [[ostrich]]. Walt Disney would later have Harpo (with Groucho and Chico) appear as one of King Cole's \"Fiddlers Three\" in the Silly Symphony ''[[Mother Goose Goes Hollywood]]''.\n\nHarpo was also caricatured in ''[[Popeye the Sailor filmography (Fleischer Studios)#1934|Sock-A-Bye Baby]]'' (1934), an early episode of the ''[[Popeye]]'' cartoon series created by [[Fleischer Studios]]. Harpo is playing the harp, and wakes up Popeye's baby, and then Popeye kills him. (After Popeye hits him, a halo appears over his head and he floats to the sky.)\n\n[[Friz Freleng]]'s 1936 [[Merrie Melodies]] cartoon ''[[The Coo-Coo Nut Grove]]'' featuring animal versions of assorted celebrities, caricatures Harpo as a bird with a red [[beak]]. When he first appears, he is chasing a woman, but the woman later turns out to be Groucho.\n\nHarpo also took an interest in painting, and a few of his works can be seen in his autobiography. In the book, Marx tells a story about how he tried to paint a nude female model, but froze up because he simply did not know how to paint properly. The model took pity on him, however, showing him a few basic strokes with a brush, until finally Harpo (fully clothed) took the model's place as the subject and the naked woman painted ''his'' portrait.<ref>Marx 1961, pp. 204\u2013205.</ref>\n\nHarpo recorded an album of harp music for [[RCA Victor]] (''Harp by Harpo'', 1952) and two for [[Mercury Records]] (''Harpo in Hi-Fi'', 1957; ''Harpo at Work'', 1958).\n\nHarpo made television appearances through the 1950s and 60s, including a 1955 episode of ''[[I Love Lucy]],'' in which he and [[Lucille Ball]] re-enacted the famous mirror scene from the Marx Brothers movie ''[[Duck Soup (1933 film)|Duck Soup]]'' (1933).<ref>{{IMDb title|id=0609287|title=I Love Lucy: Lucy and Harpo Marx}}</ref> In this scene, they are both supposed to be Harpo, not Groucho; he stays the same and she is dressed as him. About this time, he also appeared on [[NBC]]'s ''[[The Martha Raye Show]]''. Harpo and Chico played a television anthology episode of ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' entitled \"The Incredible Jewelry Robbery\" entirely in pantomime in 1959, with a brief surprise appearance by Groucho at the end. In 1960, he appeared in an episode of ''[[The DuPont Show with June Allyson]]'' entitled \"A Silent Panic\", playing a deaf-mute who, as a \"mechanical man\" in a [[department store]] window, witnessed a gangland murder. In 1961, he made guest appearances on ''[[Today (NBC program)|The Today Show]]'', ''[[Play Your Hunch]]'', ''[[Candid Camera]]'', ''[[I've Got a Secret]]'', ''[[Here's Hollywood]]'', ''[[Art Linkletter's House Party]]'', Groucho's quiz show ''[[You Bet Your Life]]'', ''[[The Ed Sullivan Show]]'', and ''Your Surprise Package'' to publicize his [[autobiography]] ''Harpo Speaks!''.\n\nIn November 1961 he guest-starred with [[Carol Burnett]] in an installment of ''[[The DuPont Show of the Week]]'' entitled \"The Wonderful World of Toys\". The show was filmed in [[Central Park]] and featured Marx playing \"[[Autumn Leaves (1945 song)|Autumn Leaves]]\" on the harp. Other stars appearing in the episode included [[Eva Gabor]], [[Audrey Meadows]], [[Mitch Miller]] and [[Milton Berle]]. A visit to the set inspired poet [[Robert Lowell]] to compose a poem about Marx.\n\nHarpo's two final television appearances came less than a month apart in late 1962. He portrayed a guardian angel on [[Columbia Broadcasting System|CBS]]'s ''[[The Red Skelton Show]]'' on September 25. He guest starred as himself on October 20 in the episode \"Musicale\" of [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s ''[[Mr. Smith Goes to Washington (TV series)|Mr. Smith Goes to Washington]]'', a [[sitcom]] starring [[Fess Parker]], based on the 1939 [[Frank Capra]] film.<ref>{{cite news| last=Hickey| first=Matthew| title=TV's Silent Panic: Harpo Marx & the Golden Age of Television| magazine=Filmfax| pages=64\u201369| date=May\u2013June 1996| url= |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[Image:Harpo & kids.jpg|thumb|Harpo Marx and three of his children wearing Harpo wigs in Los Angeles, 1954]]\nHarpo married actress [[Susan Fleming]] on September 28, 1936. The wedding became public knowledge after President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] sent the couple a telegram of congratulations the following month.<ref>{{cite news| title=Harpo Marx Weds - Marriage to Susan Fleming Is Revealed In Wire to Roosevelt| url=http://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1936/11/05/93531576.html?pageNumber=34| accessdate=15 August 2016| newspaper=The New York Times| agency=[[Associated Press]]| date=November 5, 1936| page=34}}</ref> Harpo's marriage, like Gummo's, was lifelong. (Groucho was divorced three times, Zeppo twice, Chico once.) The couple adopted four children: [[Bill Marx (pianist)|Bill]], Alex, Jimmy, and Minnie. When he was asked by [[George Burns]] in 1948 how many children he planned to adopt, he answered, \"I\u2019d like to adopt as many children as I have windows in my house. So when I leave for work, I want a kid in every window, waving goodbye.\"<ref>{{cite web| first=Cathy| last=Amerling| url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921132525/http://www.harpomarx.net/quotes.html| title=Quotes About Harpo Marx| website=Harpo Marx Tribute Site| accessdate=2020-04-10| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921055151/http://www.harpomarx.net/index.html| archivedate=2013-09-21}}</ref>\n[[File:Algonquin Round Table.gif|left|thumb|Members and associates of the Algonquin Round Table: (''standing, left to right'') [[Art Samuels]] and Harpo Marx; (''sitting'') [[Charles MacArthur]], [[Dorothy Parker]], and [[Alexander Woollcott]]]]\nHarpo was good friends with theater critic [[Alexander Woollcott]], and became a regular member of the [[Algonquin Round Table]]. He once said his main contribution was to be the audience for the quips of other members. In their play ''[[The Man Who Came to Dinner]]'', [[George S. Kaufman]] and [[Moss Hart]] based the character of \"Banjo\" on Harpo. Harpo later played the role in Los Angeles opposite Woollcott, who had inspired the character of Sheridan Whiteside.<ref>{{cite news| last=Batistick| first=Mike| title=The Man Who Came to Bubby's: Nathan Lane Takes on Critics| url=https://observer.com/2000/07/the-man-who-came-to-bubbys-nathan-lane-takes-on-critics/| newspaper=[[The New York Observer]]| date=July 24, 2000| accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Marx Brothers 1948.jpg|thumb|The Marx Brothers (clockwise: Groucho, Chico, and Harpo Marx) by [[Yousuf Karsh]] in 1948]]\nIn 1961 Harpo published his autobiography, ''Harpo Speaks!''. Because he never spoke a word in character, many believed he actually was [[Muteness|mute]]. In fact, radio and TV news recordings of his voice can be found on the Internet, in documentaries, and on bonus materials of Marx Brothers DVDs. A reporter who interviewed him in the early 1930s wrote that \"he [Harpo] ... had a deep and distinguished voice, like a professional announcer\", and like his brothers, spoke with a [[New York accent]] his entire life.<ref>{{cite audio| url=http://www.marx-brothers.org/biography/harposp.htm| title=Harpo Speaks| website=The Marx Brothers| accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref> According to those who personally knew him, Harpo's voice was much deeper than Groucho's, but it also sounded very similar to Chico's. His son, Bill, recalled that in private Harpo had a very deep and mature soft-spoken voice, but that he was \"not verbose\" like the other Marx brothers; Harpo preferred listening and learning from others.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.journalnow.com/relishnow/film_tv/tv_tidbits/marx-brothers-featured-in-new-dvd-release/article_1bfaf4ba-106a-57a5-b8bf-bc29fd7732ef.html| title=Marx Brothers featured in new DVD release| last=Clodfelter| first=Tim| newspaper=[[Winston-Salem Journal]]| date=August 17, 2014| accessdate=2014-09-02}}</ref>\n\nHarpo's final public appearance came on January 19, 1963, with singer/comedian [[Allan Sherman]]. Sherman burst into tears when Harpo announced his retirement from the entertainment business. Comedian [[Steve Allen]], who was in the audience, remembered that Harpo spoke for several minutes about his career, and how he would miss it all, and repeatedly interrupted Sherman when he tried to speak. The audience found it charmingly ironic, Allen said, that Harpo, who had never before spoken on stage or screen, \"wouldn't shut up!\"<ref name=colvin>{{cite journal| last=Colvin| first=Rod| title=Remembering Harpo: His Life and Legacy| journal=American Harp Journal| date=Winter 2009| url=https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-217240691/remembering-harpo-his-life-and-legacy| volume=22| number=2| page=36}}</ref> Harpo, an avid croquet player, was inducted into the [[Croquet Hall of Fame]] in 1979.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.croquetamerica.com/usca/halloffame/| title=United States Croquet Hall of Fame| website=[[United States Croquet Association]]| accessdate=February 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nHarpo Marx died on September 28, 1964, (his 28th wedding anniversary), at age 75 in a West Los Angeles hospital, one day after undergoing heart surgery.<ref name=\"NYT obituary\">{{cite news| title=Harpo Marx, the Silent Comedian, Is Dead at 70| url=https://www.nytimes.com/1964/09/29/harpo-marx-the-silent-comedian-is-dead-at-70.html| accessdate=15 August 2016| newspaper=The New York Times| agency=Associated Press| date=September 29, 1964| page=1}}</ref> Harpo's death was said to have hit the surviving Marx brothers very hard. Groucho's son [[Arthur Marx]], who attended the funeral with most of the Marx family, later said that Harpo's funeral was the only time in his life that he ever saw his father cry. In his will, Harpo Marx donated his trademark harp to the State of [[Israel]].<ref name=\"Mitchell\" /> His remains were cremated, and his ashes were scattered at a golf course in [[Rancho Mirage, California]].\n\n==Legacy==\nHarpo is most known for his signature outfit: trench coat with over-large pockets, red wig (he switched to a blonde one for every film after ''The Cocoanuts''), top hat, and a comical horn heard in his movies. He was also well known for playing the harp, though he could not read music. Outside the professional harp community, he remains one of the best \"ambassadors for the harp\" the world has known and one of his harps was donated to an Israeli orchestra. In time, his talent earned him an international reputation as he performed in movies as well as in stage shows around the globe.<ref name=colvin/> His musical talent extended to beyond the harp, to piano, clarinet, etc...all mostly learned independent of professional instruction.\n\nIn 2002, a Golden Palm Star on the [[Palm Springs, California]], [[Palm Springs Walk of Stars|Walk of Stars]] was dedicated to him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.palmspringswalkofstars.com/web-storage/Stars/Stars%20dedicated%20by%20date.pdf |title=Palm Springs Walk of Stars by date dedicated |format=PDF |accessdate=2013-09-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013165655/http://www.palmspringswalkofstars.com/web-storage/Stars/Stars%20dedicated%20by%20date.pdf |archivedate=2012-10-13 }}</ref>\n\n===Film portrayal===\nMarx was portrayed by the actor J.M. Henry in the film ''[[Mrs. Parker and the Vicious Circle]]''.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0110588/fullcredits#cast| website=IMDb| title=Mrs. Parker and the Vicious Circle: Full Cast & Crew}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical portrayals===\nMarx was portrayed by actor Daniel Fortus in the Broadway production of ''[[Minnie's Boys]]'', a [[Broadway musical]] that ran for 64 performances at the [[Imperial Theatre]] from March to May 1970.<ref>{{cite web| title=Minnie's Boys| website=IMDb| url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-production/minnies-boys-3517}}</ref> The show focused on the early days of the Marx Brothers' act and the importance of their mother Minnie's strong hand in guiding and molding them into a successful vaudeville and film comedy team.\n\nActress Patricia Lopez played Harpo in a send-up of Hollywood movie making, the 1980 Broadway production, \"[[A Day in Hollywood/A Night in the Ukraine]]\", for which she won a Tony Award for Best Performance by a Featured Actress in a Musical.\n\nHe was also portrayed by Les Marsden in ''[[Groucho: A Life in Revue]]'', which appeared [[off-Broadway]] at the [[Lucille Lortel]] Theatre. The show ran for 264 performances from October 1986 through May 1987.\n\n===References in music===\n[[Jonathan Richman]] references Harpo in his song ''When Harpo Played His Harp''.\n\n[[Neil Cicierega|Lemon Demon]] references Harpo Marx in the song ''Vow of Silence''.\n\n[[Phoebe Snow]]'s ''Harpo's Blues'' (1975) was written about \"a guy in a band who ''became'' Harpo Marx ... he wouldn't talk, and his eyes would roll around ... \"<ref>{{cite journal| last=Palmer| first=Robert| title=Phoebe Snow Finds the Suburbs of the Soul| journal=[[Rolling Stone]]| date=April 26, 2011| url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/phoebe-snow-finds-the-suburbs-of-the-soul-rolling-stones-1975-cover-story-20110426}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and honors===\nIn the [[46th Academy Awards|1974 Academy Awards telecast]], [[Jack Lemmon]] presented Groucho with an honorary [[Academy Award]] to a standing ovation. The award was also on behalf of Harpo, Chico, and Zeppo, whom Lemmon mentioned by name. It was one of Groucho's final major public appearances.  \"I wish that Harpo and Chico could be here to share with me this great honor,\" he said, naming the two deceased brothers (Zeppo and Gummo were still alive at the time). Groucho also praised the late [[Margaret Dumont]] as a great straight woman who never understood any of his jokes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a1YsAxiiH98 |title=Groucho Marx receiving an Honorary Oscar\u00ae |publisher=Oscars.org |date=2009-11-24 |accessdate=2018-08-17}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1921|| ''[[Humor Risk]]'' || Watson || Short, lost\n|-\n|1925|| ''[[Too Many Kisses]]'' || The Village Peter Pan ||\n|-\n|1929|| ''[[The Cocoanuts]]'' || Harpo ||\n|-\n|1930|| ''[[Animal Crackers (1930 film)|Animal Crackers]]'' || The Professor ||\n|-\n|1931|| ''[[The House That Shadows Built]]'' || The Merchant of Wieners ||\n|-\n|1931|| ''[[Monkey Business (1931 film)|Monkey Business]]'' || Harpo ||\n|-\n|1932|| ''[[Hollywood on Parade]], #A-5'' || Himself || Short\n|-\n|1932|| ''[[Horse Feathers]]'' || Pinky ||\n|-\n|1932|| ''[[Hollywood on Parade]], #11'' || Himself || Short\n|-\n|1933|| ''[[Duck Soup (1933 film)|Duck Soup]]'' || Pinky ||\n|-\n|1935|| ''[[A Night at the Opera (film)|A Night at the Opera]]'' || Tomasso ||\n|-\n|1935|| ''[[La Fiesta de Santa Barbara]]'' || Himself || Short\n|-\n|1937|| ''[[A Day at the Races (film)|A Day at the Races]]'' || Stuffy ||\n|-\n|1938|| ''[[Room Service (1938 film)|Room Service]]'' || Faker Englund ||\n|-\n|1939|| ''[[At The Circus]]'' || 'Punchy' ||\n|-\n|1940|| ''[[Go West (1940 film)|Go West]]'' || 'Rusty' Panello ||\n|-\n|1941|| ''[[The Big Store]]'' || Wacky ||\n|-\n|1943|| ''[[Stage Door Canteen (film)|Stage Door Canteen]]'' || Harpo Marx ||\n|-\n|1945|| ''All Star Bond Rally'' || Himself ||\n|-\n|1946|| ''[[A Night in Casablanca]]'' || Rusty ||\n|-\n|1949|| ''[[Love Happy]]'' || Harpo ||\n|-\n|1957|| ''[[The Story of Mankind (film)|The Story of Mankind]]'' || Sir Isaac Newton ||\n|-\n|1962|| ''Got It Made'' || || lost<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.harposplace.com/Character/CharacterFilm.php| title=Harpo Marx Filmography| website=HarposPlace.com| accessdate=21 September 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===TV===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1952|| ''The [[Ezio Pinza]] Show'' || Himself - Comic Actor || 1 episode\n|-\n|1952-1953|| ''[[All Star Revue]]'' || Himself || 3 episodes\n|-\n|1953|| ''Season's Greetings'' || Himself || TV movie\n|-\n|1954|| ''[[The Colgate Comedy Hour]]'' || Governor || 1 episode\n|-\n|1955|| ''[[I Love Lucy]]'' || Himself || 1 episode\n|-\n|1957|| ''[[Playhouse 90]]'' || || 1 episode\n|-\n|1958|| ''[[The DuPont Show of the Month]]'' || Narrator || 1 episode\n|-\n|1959|| ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' || Nick || 1 episode\n|-\n|1960|| ''[[The DuPont Show with June Allyson]]'' || Benson || 1 episode\n|-\n|1961|| ''[[The DuPont Show of the Week]]'' || Himself || Episode: The Wonderful World of Toys\n|-\n|1962|| ''[[The Red Skelton Hour]]'' || Guardian Angel || 1 episode\n|-\n|1962|| ''[[Mr. Smith Goes to Washington (TV series)|Mr. Smith Goes to Washington]]'' || Himself || 1 episode, (final appearance)\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n*1952 ''Harp By Harpo''\n*1957 ''Harpo in Hi-Fi''\n*1958 ''Harpo At Work!''\n\n==Bibliography==\n*1961 ''Harpo Speaks!''\n*2000 ''Harpo Speaks ...About New York'' (the first two chapters of the above, repackaged)\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n* Adamson, Joe (1973). ''Groucho, Harpo, Chico and Sometimes Zeppo: A Celebration of the Marx Brothers''. New York: Simon & Schuster. {{ISBN|0-671-21458-6}}\n* Marx, Harpo (1961). ''Harpo Speaks!''. New York: B. Geis Associates; New York: Limelight Editions, 1985. {{ISBN|0-879-10036-2}}\n* Mitchell, Glenn (1996). ''The Marx Brothers Encyclopedia''. London: B.T. Batsford Ltd. {{ISBN|0-713-47838-1}}\n* Koestenbaum, Wayne (2012). ''The Anatomy of Harpo Marx''. Berkeley: University of California Press. {{ISBN|978-0-520-26900-2}}\n* Fix, Charlene (2013) ''Harpo Marx asTrickster. ''Jefferson, North Carolina: McFarland Publishers Inc. {{ISBN|978-0-786-47147-8}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* [http://www.harposplace.com/ Harpo Marx family website, run by his son Bill]\n* {{IMDb name|555617|Harpo Marx}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{Find a Grave|679}}\n{{Marx Brothers}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marx, Harpo}}\n[[Category:1888 births]]\n[[Category:1964 deaths]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American comedy musicians]]\n[[Category:American harpists]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American male comedy actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American mimes]]\n[[Category:American people of French-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of German-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:American Zionists]]\n[[Category:Comedians from New York City]]\n[[Category:Jewish American comedians]]\n[[Category:Jewish American male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New York City]]\n[[Category:Marx Brothers]]\n[[Category:People from the Upper East Side]]\n[[Category:RCA Victor artists]]\n[[Category:Vaudeville performers]]\n[[Category:Whistlers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American comedian}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Harpo Marx\n| image        = Harpo_Marx_1948.jpg\n| imagesize    = 200px\n| caption      = Harpo Marx in 1948\n| birth_name   = Adolph Marx\n| birth_date   = {{birth date|1888|11|23}}\n| birth_place = [[Manhattan]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| death_date   = {{death date and age|1964|09|28|1888|11|23}}\n| death_place  = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation   = {{hlist|Comedian|actor|mime artist|musician}}\n| years_active = 1910\u20131963\n| height       = 5 ft 5 1/2 in (1.66 m)\n| parents      = {{ubl|[[Sam Marx|Sam \"Frenchie\" Marx]]|[[Minnie Marx|Minnie Sch\u00f6nberg]]}}\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Susan Fleming]]|1936<!--As marriage ended with his death, year is omitted per Template:Marriage instructions--->}} \n| children     = 4 \n| relatives    = {{ubl|[[Groucho Marx]] (brother)|[[Chico Marx]] (brother)|[[Gummo Marx]] (brother)|[[Zeppo Marx]] (brother)|[[Al Shean]] (maternal uncle)}}\n}}\n\n'''Arthur''' \"'''Harpo'''\" '''Marx''' (born '''Adolph Marx'''; November 23, 1888 \u2013 September 28, 1964) was an American [[comedian]], actor, [[mime artist]], and musician, and the second-oldest of the [[Marx Brothers]]. In contrast to the mainly verbal comedy of his brothers [[Groucho Marx]] and [[Chico Marx]], Harpo's comic style was visual, being an example of both [[clown]] and [[pantomime]] traditions. He wore a curly reddish blonde wig, and never spoke during performances (he blew a horn or [[Whistling|whistled]] to communicate). He frequently used [[Theatrical property|props]] such as a horn cane, made up of a pipe, tape, and a bulbhorn, and he played the [[harp]] in most of his films.<ref name=\"birth\">{{cite web| title=Harpo Marx| website=Biography| url=https://www.biography.com/people/harpo-marx-16242175|date=April 2, 2014| accessdate=4 August 2018}}{{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nHarpo was born on November 23, 1888, in [[Manhattan]]. He grew up in a neighborhood now known as [[Carnegie Hill]] on the [[Upper East Side]] of Manhattan, on East 93rd Street off [[Lexington Avenue]]. The turn-of-the-century tenement that Harpo later called (in his autobiography ''Harpo Speaks!'') \"the first real home I can remember\" was populated with European immigrants, mostly artisans\u2014which even included a glass blower. Just across the street were the oldest [[brownstone]]s in the area, owned by people like [[David L. Loew]] and William Orth.\n\nHarpo's parents were [[Sam Marx]] (called \"Frenchie\" throughout his life) and his wife, [[Minnie Marx|Minnie Schoenberg Marx]]. Minnie's brother was [[Al Shean]]. Marx's family was Jewish. His mother was from [[East Frisia]] in Germany, and his father was a native of Alsace in [[France]] and worked as a tailor.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://judaisme.sdv.fr/perso/marxbr/geneal.htm| title=La famille paternelle des Marx Brothers| website=Judaisme.sdv.fr| language=French| trans-title=The Paternal Family of the Marx Brothers| website=Circle of Jewish Geneology| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title=Mrs. Minnie Marx. Mother of Four Marx Brothers, Musical Comedy Stars, Dies| newspaper=[[The New York Times]]| url=http://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1929/09/16/95997162.html?pageNumber=21| date=September 16, 1929| page=21| accessdate=2016-08-09| url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nHarpo received little formal education and left grade school at age eight (mainly due to bullying)<ref name=\"speaks\"/> during his second attempt to pass the second grade. He began to work, gaining employment in numerous odd jobs alongside his brother [[Chico Marx|Chico]] to contribute to the family income, including selling newspapers, working in a butcher shop, and as an errand office boy.<ref>Marx 1961, pp. 17\u201319</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===On stage===\nIn January 1910, Harpo joined two of his brothers, [[Groucho Marx|Julius]] (later \"Groucho\") and [[Gummo Marx|Milton]] (later \"Gummo\"), to form \"The Three Nightingales\", later changed to simply \"The Marx Brothers\". Multiple stories\u2014most unsubstantiated\u2014exist to explain Harpo's evolution as the \"silent\" character in the brothers' act. In his memoir, Groucho wrote that Harpo simply wasn't very good at memorizing dialogue, and thus was ideal for the role of the \"dunce who couldn't speak\", a common character in vaudeville acts of the time.<ref>Marx, Groucho (1959). Groucho And Me. Da Capo Press. {{ISBN|978-0-306-80666-7}}, p. 46.</ref>\n\nHarpo gained his stage name during a card game at the Orpheum Theatre in [[Galesburg, Illinois]]. The dealer (Art Fisher) called him \"Harpo\" because he played the [[harp]].<ref name=\"speaks\">{{cite book| last=Marx| first=Harpo| author2=Rowland Barber| title=Harpo Speaks!| publisher=Limelight Editions| year=1988| location=New York| isbn=978-0879100360| url=https://archive.org/details/harpospeaks00marx}}</ref><ref name=\"Mitchell p169\">Mitchell 1996, p. 169</ref> He learned how to hold it properly from a picture of an angel playing a harp that he saw in a [[five-and-dime]]. No one in town knew how to play the harp, so Harpo tuned it as best he could, starting with one basic note and tuning it from there. Three years later he found out he had tuned it incorrectly, but he could not have tuned it properly; if he had, the strings would have broken each night. Harpo's method placed much less tension on the strings.{{citation needed|date=December 2011}} Although he played this way for the rest of his life, he did try to learn how to play correctly, and he spent considerable money hiring the best teachers. They spent their time listening to him, fascinated by the way he played.<ref name=\"speaks\"/> The major exception was [[Mildred Dilling]], a professional harpist who did teach Harpo the proper techniques of the instrument and collaborated with him regularly when he had difficulty with various compositions.<ref>{{cite news| title=Mildred Dilling, 88, a Harpist, Performed for 5 Presidents| url=https://www.nytimes.com/1983/01/03/obituaries/mildred-dilling-88-a-harpist-performed-for-5-presidents.html| accessdate=23 January 2018| newspaper=The New York Times| date=3 January 1983}}</ref>\n\nIn the autobiography ''Harpo Speaks!'' (1961), he recounts how [[Chico Marx|Chico]] found him jobs playing [[piano]] to accompany [[silent film|silent movies]]. Unlike Chico, Harpo could play only two songs on the piano, \"Waltz Me Around Again, Willie\" and \"Love Me and the World Is Mine,\" but he adapted this small repertoire in different tempos to suit the action on the screen. He was also seen playing a portion of Rachmaninoff's \"Prelude in C# minor\" in ''[[A Day at the Races (film)|A Day at the Races]]'' and chords on the piano in ''[[A Night at the Opera (film)|A Night at the Opera]]'', in such a way that the piano sounded much like a harp, as a prelude to actually playing the harp in that scene.\n\nHarpo had changed his name from Adolph to Arthur by 1911. This was due primarily to his dislike for the name Adolph (as a child, he was routinely called \"Ahdie\" instead). The name change may have also happened because of the similarity between Harpo's name and Adolph Marks, a prominent show business attorney in Chicago.<ref>{{cite book| last=Bader| first=Robert S.| title=Four of the Three Musketeers| publisher=Northwestern University Press| year=2016| location=Evanston, IL| page=147 |isbn=978-0-8101-3416-4}}</ref> [[Urban legends]] stating that the name change came about during [[World War I]] due to anti-German sentiment in the US, or during [[World War II]] because of the stigma that [[Adolf Hitler]] imposed on the name, are groundless.<ref>{{cite web| last=Mikkelson| first=Barbara and David| title=Lane Kibe| website=[[Snopes]]| date=2007-08-09| url=http://www.snopes.com/movies/actors/harpo.htm| accessdate=2008-01-01}}</ref>\n\n===On film===\n[[File:Harpo Marx playing the harp.jpeg|thumb|left|Harpo Marx playing the harp]]\nHis first screen appearance was in the film ''[[Humor Risk]]'' (1921), with his brothers, although according to Groucho, it was only screened once and then [[Lost film|lost]]. Four years later, Harpo appeared without his brothers in ''[[Too Many Kisses]]'' (1925), four years before the brothers' first released film, ''[[The Cocoanuts]]'' (1929). In ''Too Many Kisses'', Harpo spoke the only line he would ever speak on-camera in a movie: \"You sure you can't move?\"<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.marx-brothers.org/watching/film/Too_Many_Kisses.htm| title=Too Many Kisses (1925)| website=Marx-brothers.org| access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref> (said to the film's tied-up hero before punching him). Fittingly, it was a silent movie, and the audience saw only his lips move and the line on a title card.\n\nHarpo was often cast as Chico's eccentric partner-in-crime, whom he would often help by playing charades to tell of Groucho's problem, and/or annoy by giving Chico his leg, either to give it a rest or as an alternative to a handshake.\n\n[[File:Marx Brothers 1931.jpg|thumb|From top: Chico, Harpo, Groucho, and Zeppo, ca. 1931]]\nHarpo became known for prop-laden [[Visual gag|sight gags]], in particular the seemingly [[Hammerspace|infinite number of odd things]] stored in his [[Overcoat|topcoat]]'s oversized pockets. In the film ''[[Horse Feathers]]'' (1932), Groucho, referring to an impossible situation, tells Harpo that he cannot \"burn the candle at both ends.\" Harpo immediately produces from within his coat pocket a lit candle burning at both ends. In the same film, a homeless man on the street asks Harpo for money for a cup of coffee, and he subsequently produces a steaming cup, complete with saucer, from inside his coat. Also in ''Horse Feathers'', he has a fish and a sword, and when he wants to go to his speakeasy, he stabs the fish in its mouth with his sword to give the password, \"Swordfish.\" In ''Duck Soup'', he produces a lit blowtorch to light a cigar. As author Joe Adamson put in his book, ''Groucho, Harpo, Chico and Sometimes Zeppo'', \"The president of the college has been shouted down by a mute.\"\n\nHarpo often used facial expressions and mime to get his point across. One of his facial expressions, which he used in every Marx Brothers film and stage play, beginning with ''Fun in Hi Skule'', was known as \"the Gookie.\" Harpo created it by mimicking the expression of Mr. Gehrke, a New York tobacconist who would make a similar face while concentrating on rolling cigars.<ref name=\"speaks\"/><ref name=\"Mitchell\">{{cite book| last=Mitchell| first=Glenn| title=The Marx Brothers Encyclopedia| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=e28dAQAAIAAJ&dq=the+marx+brothers+encyclopedia&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=gehrke| publisher=Reynolds & Hearn| year=2003| location=London| page=123| isbn=978-1903111499| url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nHarpo further distinguished his character by wearing a \"fright wig\". Early in his career it was dyed pink, as evidenced by color film posters of the time and by allusions to it in films, with character names such as \"Pinky\" in ''Duck Soup''. It tended to show as blonde on-screen due to the black-and-white film stock at the time. Over time, he darkened the pink to more of a reddish color, again films alluded to it with character names such as \"Rusty\".\n\nHis non-speaking in his early films was occasionally referred to by the other Marx Brothers, who were careful to imply that his character's not speaking was a choice rather than a disability. They would make joking reference to this part of his act. For example, in ''[[Animal Crackers (1930 film)|Animal Crackers]]'' his character was ironically dubbed \"The Professor\". In ''The Cocoanuts'', this exchange occurred:\n\n'''Groucho''': \"Who is this?\"\n\n'''Chico''': \"Dat's-a my partner, but he no speak.\"\n\n'''Groucho''': \"Oh, that's your [[wikt:silent partner|silent partner]]!\"\n\nIn later films, Harpo was repeatedly put in situations where he attempted to convey a vital message by whistling and pantomime, reinforcing the idea that his character was unable to speak.\n\nThe Marxes' film ''At the Circus (1939)'' contains a unique scene where Harpo is ostensibly heard saying \"A-choo!\" twice, as he sneezes. It is unclear, however, whether he actually voiced the line, or if he mimed it while someone said it off-camera.  \n\n===In other media===\n[[File:Harpo and Chico Marx General Electric Theater 1959.JPG|thumb|right|Harpo and Chico Marx in \"The Incredible Jewelry Robbery\" (1959)]]\n[[File:Harpo Marx Silent Panic DuPont Show 1960.JPG|thumb|right|Marx as the \"mechanical man\" in \"A Silent Panic\" (1960)]]\nIn 1933, following U.S. diplomatic recognition of the [[Soviet Union]], he spent six weeks in [[Moscow]] as a performer and goodwill ambassador.<ref name=\"speaks\" /> His tour was a huge success. Harpo's name was transliterated into Russian, using the Cyrillic alphabet, as \u0425\u0410\u0420\u041f\u041e \u041c\u0410\u0420\u041a\u0421, and was billed as such during his Soviet Union appearances. Harpo, having no knowledge of Russian, pronounced it as \"Exapno Mapcase\". At that time Harpo and the Soviet Foreign Minister [[Maxim Litvinov]] became friends and even performed a routine on stage together.<ref>''Current Biography 1941, pp 518\u201320.</ref> During this time he served as a secret courier; delivering communiques to and from the US embassy in Moscow at the request of Ambassador [[William Christian Bullitt, Jr.]], smuggling the messages in and out of Russia by taping a sealed envelope to his leg beneath his trousers, an event described in [[David Fromkin]]'s 1995 book ''In the Time of the Americans''.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=O1UNAAAAIBAJ&sjid=im4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=3199,8313638&dq=harpo-marx+soviet-union+courier \"At Our Best\"], ''[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]'', July 30, 1995. Accessed July 29, 2009.{{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref><ref>[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-26993299_ITM \"Was Harpo Marx The Silent Spy Who Stole Soviet Secrets?\"], ''Europe Intelligence Wire'', December 28, 2002. Accessed July 29, 2009.</ref> In ''Harpo Speaks!'', Marx describes his relief at making it out of the Soviet Union, recalling how \"I pulled up my pants, ripped off the tape, unwound the straps, handed over the dispatches from Ambassador Bullitt, and gave my leg its first scratch in ten days.\"<ref>Marx 1961, p. 336.</ref>\n\nThe Russia trip was later memorialized in a bizarre science fiction novella, ''The Foreign Hand Tie'' by [[Randall Garrett]], a tale of telepathic spies which is full of references to the Marx Brothers and their films.<ref>{{cite journal| first=Randall| last=Garrett| url=http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/30497| title=The Foreign Hand Tie| journal=[[Analog (magazine)|Analog]]| date=December 1961| via=[[Project Gutenberg]]| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> (The title itself is a Marx-like pun on the dual ideas of a \"foreign hand\" and a style of neckwear known as a \"[[four-in-hand knot|four-in-hand tie]].\")\n\nIn 1936, he was one of a number of performers and celebrities to appear as [[caricature]]s in the [[The Walt Disney Company|Walt Disney Production]] of ''[[Mickey's Polo Team]]''. Harpo was part of a team of [[polo]]-playing [[movie stars]] which included [[Charlie Chaplin]] and [[Laurel and Hardy]]. His mount was an [[ostrich]]. Walt Disney would later have Harpo (with Groucho and Chico) appear as one of King Cole's \"Fiddlers Three\" in the Silly Symphony ''[[Mother Goose Goes Hollywood]]''.\n\nHarpo was also caricatured in ''[[Popeye the Sailor filmography (Fleischer Studios)#1934|Sock-A-Bye Baby]]'' (1934), an early episode of the ''[[Popeye]]'' cartoon series created by [[Fleischer Studios]]. Harpo is playing the harp, and wakes up Popeye's baby, and then Popeye kills him. (After Popeye hits him, a halo appears over his head and he floats to the sky.)\n\n[[Friz Freleng]]'s 1936 [[Merrie Melodies]] cartoon ''[[The Coo-Coo Nut Grove]]'' featuring animal versions of assorted celebrities, caricatures Harpo as a bird with a red [[beak]]. When he first appears, he is chasing a woman, but the woman later turns out to be Groucho.\n\nHarpo also took an interest in painting, and a few of his works can be seen in his autobiography. In the book, Marx tells a story about how he tried to paint a nude female model, but froze up because he simply did not know how to paint properly. The model took pity on him, however, showing him a few basic strokes with a brush, until finally Harpo (fully clothed) took the model's place as the subject and the naked woman painted ''his'' portrait.<ref>Marx 1961, pp. 204\u2013205.</ref>\n\nHarpo recorded an album of harp music for [[RCA Victor]] (''Harp by Harpo'', 1952) and two for [[Mercury Records]] (''Harpo in Hi-Fi'', 1957; ''Harpo at Work'', 1958).\n\nHarpo made television appearances through the 1950s and 60s, including a 1955 episode of ''[[I Love Lucy]],'' in which he and [[Lucille Ball]] re-enacted the famous mirror scene from the Marx Brothers movie ''[[Duck Soup (1933 film)|Duck Soup]]'' (1933).<ref>{{IMDb title|id=0609287|title=I Love Lucy: Lucy and Harpo Marx}}</ref> In this scene, they are both supposed to be Harpo, not Groucho; he stays the same and she is dressed as him. About this time, he also appeared on [[NBC]]'s ''[[The Martha Raye Show]]''. Harpo and Chico played a television anthology episode of ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' entitled \"The Incredible Jewelry Robbery\" entirely in pantomime in 1959, with a brief surprise appearance by Groucho at the end. In 1960, he appeared in an episode of ''[[The DuPont Show with June Allyson]]'' entitled \"A Silent Panic\", playing a deaf-mute who, as a \"mechanical man\" in a [[department store]] window, witnessed a gangland murder. In 1961, he made guest appearances on ''[[Today (NBC program)|The Today Show]]'', ''[[Play Your Hunch]]'', ''[[Candid Camera]]'', ''[[I've Got a Secret]]'', ''[[Here's Hollywood]]'', ''[[Art Linkletter's House Party]]'', Groucho's quiz show ''[[You Bet Your Life]]'', ''[[The Ed Sullivan Show]]'', and ''Your Surprise Package'' to publicize his [[autobiography]] ''Harpo Speaks!''.\n\nIn November 1961 he guest-starred with [[Carol Burnett]] in an installment of ''[[The DuPont Show of the Week]]'' entitled \"The Wonderful World of Toys\". The show was filmed in [[Central Park]] and featured Marx playing \"[[Autumn Leaves (1945 song)|Autumn Leaves]]\" on the harp. Other stars appearing in the episode included [[Eva Gabor]], [[Audrey Meadows]], [[Mitch Miller]] and [[Milton Berle]]. A visit to the set inspired poet [[Robert Lowell]] to compose a poem about Marx.\n\nHarpo's two final television appearances came less than a month apart in late 1962. He portrayed a guardian angel on [[Columbia Broadcasting System|CBS]]'s ''[[The Red Skelton Show]]'' on September 25. He guest starred as himself on October 20 in the episode \"Musicale\" of [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s ''[[Mr. Smith Goes to Washington (TV series)|Mr. Smith Goes to Washington]]'', a [[sitcom]] starring [[Fess Parker]], based on the 1939 [[Frank Capra]] film.<ref>{{cite news| last=Hickey| first=Matthew| title=TV's Silent Panic: Harpo Marx & the Golden Age of Television| magazine=Filmfax| pages=64\u201369| date=May\u2013June 1996| url= |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n[[Image:Harpo & kids.jpg|thumb|Harpo Marx and three of his children wearing Harpo wigs in Los Angeles, 1954]]\nHarpo married actress [[Susan Fleming]] on September 28, 1936. The wedding became public knowledge after President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] sent the couple a telegram of congratulations the following month.<ref>{{cite news| title=Harpo Marx Weds - Marriage to Susan Fleming Is Revealed In Wire to Roosevelt| url=http://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1936/11/05/93531576.html?pageNumber=34| accessdate=15 August 2016| newspaper=The New York Times| agency=[[Associated Press]]| date=November 5, 1936| page=34}}</ref> Harpo's marriage, like Gummo's, was lifelong. (Groucho was divorced three times, Zeppo twice, Chico once.) The couple adopted four children: [[Bill Marx (pianist)|Bill]], Alex, Jimmy, and Minnie. When he was asked by [[George Burns]] in 1948 how many children he planned to adopt, he answered, \"I\u2019d like to adopt as many children as I have windows in my house. So when I leave for work, I want a kid in every window, waving goodbye.\"<ref>{{cite web| first=Cathy| last=Amerling| url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921132525/http://www.harpomarx.net/quotes.html| title=Quotes About Harpo Marx| website=Harpo Marx Tribute Site| accessdate=2020-04-10| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921055151/http://www.harpomarx.net/index.html| archivedate=2013-09-21}}</ref>\n[[File:Algonquin Round Table.gif|left|thumb|Members and associates of the Algonquin Round Table: (''standing, left to right'') [[Art Samuels]] and Harpo Marx; (''sitting'') [[Charles MacArthur]], [[Dorothy Parker]], and [[Alexander Woollcott]]]]\nHarpo was good friends with theater critic [[Alexander Woollcott]], and became a regular member of the [[Algonquin Round Table]]. He once said his main contribution was to be the audience for the quips of other members. In their play ''[[The Man Who Came to Dinner]]'', [[George S. Kaufman]] and [[Moss Hart]] based the character of \"Banjo\" on Harpo. Harpo later played the role in Los Angeles opposite Woollcott, who had inspired the character of Sheridan Whiteside.<ref>{{cite news| last=Batistick| first=Mike| title=The Man Who Came to Bubby's: Nathan Lane Takes on Critics| url=https://observer.com/2000/07/the-man-who-came-to-bubbys-nathan-lane-takes-on-critics/| newspaper=[[The New York Observer]]| date=July 24, 2000| accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Marx Brothers 1948.jpg|thumb|The Marx Brothers (clockwise: Groucho, Chico, and Harpo Marx) by [[Yousuf Karsh]] in 1948]]\nIn 1961 Harpo published his autobiography, ''Harpo Speaks!''. Because he never spoke a word in character, many believed he actually was [[Muteness|mute]]. In fact, radio and TV news recordings of his voice can be found on the Internet, in documentaries, and on bonus materials of Marx Brothers DVDs. A reporter who interviewed him in the early 1930s wrote that \"he [Harpo] ... had a deep and distinguished voice, like a professional announcer\", and like his brothers, spoke with a [[New York accent]] his entire life.<ref>{{cite audio| url=http://www.marx-brothers.org/biography/harposp.htm| title=Harpo Speaks| website=The Marx Brothers| accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref> According to those who personally knew him, Harpo's voice was much deeper than Groucho's, but it also sounded very similar to Chico's. His son, Bill, recalled that in private Harpo had a very deep and mature soft-spoken voice, but that he was \"not verbose\" like the other Marx brothers; Harpo preferred listening and learning from others.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.journalnow.com/relishnow/film_tv/tv_tidbits/marx-brothers-featured-in-new-dvd-release/article_1bfaf4ba-106a-57a5-b8bf-bc29fd7732ef.html| title=Marx Brothers featured in new DVD release| last=Clodfelter| first=Tim| newspaper=[[Winston-Salem Journal]]| date=August 17, 2014| accessdate=2014-09-02}}</ref>\n\nHarpo's final public appearance came on January 19, 1963, with singer/comedian [[Allan Sherman]]. Sherman burst into tears when Harpo announced his retirement from the entertainment business. Comedian [[Steve Allen]], who was in the audience, remembered that Harpo spoke for several minutes about his career, and how he would miss it all, and repeatedly interrupted Sherman when he tried to speak. The audience found it charmingly ironic, Allen said, that Harpo, who had never before spoken on stage or screen, \"wouldn't shut up!\"<ref name=colvin>{{cite journal| last=Colvin| first=Rod| title=Remembering Harpo: His Life and Legacy| journal=American Harp Journal| date=Winter 2009| url=https://www.questia.com/magazine/1G1-217240691/remembering-harpo-his-life-and-legacy| volume=22| number=2| page=36}}</ref> Harpo, an avid croquet player, was inducted into the [[Croquet Hall of Fame]] in 1979.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.croquetamerica.com/usca/halloffame/| title=United States Croquet Hall of Fame| website=[[United States Croquet Association]]| accessdate=February 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Death==\nHarpo Marx died on September 28, 1964, (his 28th wedding anniversary), at age 75 in a West Los Angeles hospital, one day after undergoing heart surgery.<ref name=\"NYT obituary\">{{cite news| title=Harpo Marx, the Silent Comedian, Is Dead at 70| url=https://www.nytimes.com/1964/09/29/harpo-marx-the-silent-comedian-is-dead-at-70.html| accessdate=15 August 2016| newspaper=The New York Times| agency=Associated Press| date=September 29, 1964| page=1}}</ref> Harpo's death was said to have hit the surviving Marx brothers very hard. Groucho's son [[Arthur Marx]], who attended the funeral with most of the Marx family, later said that Harpo's funeral was the only time in his life that he ever saw his father cry. In his will, Harpo Marx donated his trademark harp to the State of [[Israel]].<ref name=\"Mitchell\" /> His remains were cremated, and his ashes were scattered at a golf course in [[Rancho Mirage, California]].\n\n==Legacy==\nHarpo is most known for his signature outfit: trench coat with over-large pockets, red wig (he switched to a blonde one for every film after ''The Cocoanuts''), top hat, and a comical horn heard in his movies. He was also well known for playing the harp, though he could not read music. Outside the professional harp community, he remains one of the best \"ambassadors for the harp\" the world has known and one of his harps was donated to an Israeli orchestra. In time, his talent earned him an international reputation as he performed in movies as well as in stage shows around the globe.<ref name=colvin/> His musical talent extended to beyond the harp, to piano, clarinet, etc...all mostly learned independent of professional instruction.\n\nIn 2002, a Golden Palm Star on the [[Palm Springs, California]], [[Palm Springs Walk of Stars|Walk of Stars]] was dedicated to him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.palmspringswalkofstars.com/web-storage/Stars/Stars%20dedicated%20by%20date.pdf |title=Palm Springs Walk of Stars by date dedicated |format=PDF |accessdate=2013-09-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013165655/http://www.palmspringswalkofstars.com/web-storage/Stars/Stars%20dedicated%20by%20date.pdf |archivedate=2012-10-13 }}</ref>\n\n===Film portrayal===\nMarx was portrayed by the actor J.M. Henry in the film ''[[Mrs. Parker and the Vicious Circle]]''.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0110588/fullcredits#cast| website=IMDb| title=Mrs. Parker and the Vicious Circle: Full Cast & Crew}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical portrayals===\nMarx was portrayed by actor Daniel Fortus in the Broadway production of ''[[Minnie's Boys]]'', a [[Broadway musical]] that ran for 64 performances at the [[Imperial Theatre]] from March to May 1970.<ref>{{cite web| title=Minnie's Boys| website=IMDb| url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-production/minnies-boys-3517}}</ref> The show focused on the early days of the Marx Brothers' act and the importance of their mother Minnie's strong hand in guiding and molding them into a successful vaudeville and film comedy team.\n\nActress Patricia Lopez played Harpo in a send-up of Hollywood movie making, the 1980 Broadway production, \"[[A Day in Hollywood/A Night in the Ukraine]]\", for which she won a Tony Award for Best Performance by a Featured Actress in a Musical.\n\nHe was also portrayed by Les Marsden in ''[[Groucho: A Life in Revue]]'', which appeared [[off-Broadway]] at the [[Lucille Lortel]] Theatre. The show ran for 264 performances from October 1986 through May 1987.\n\n===References in music===\n[[Jonathan Richman]] references Harpo in his song ''When Harpo Played His Harp''.\n\n[[Neil Cicierega|Lemon Demon]] references Harpo Marx in the song ''Vow of Silence''.\n\n[[Phoebe Snow]]'s ''Harpo's Blues'' (1975) was written about \"a guy in a band who ''became'' Harpo Marx ... he wouldn't talk, and his eyes would roll around ... \"<ref>{{cite journal| last=Palmer| first=Robert| title=Phoebe Snow Finds the Suburbs of the Soul| journal=[[Rolling Stone]]| date=April 26, 2011| url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/phoebe-snow-finds-the-suburbs-of-the-soul-rolling-stones-1975-cover-story-20110426}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and honors===\nIn the [[46th Academy Awards|1974 Academy Awards telecast]], [[Jack Lemmon]] presented Groucho with an honorary [[Academy Award]] to a standing ovation. The award was also on behalf of Harpo, Chico, and Zeppo, whom Lemmon mentioned by name. It was one of Groucho's final major public appearances.  \"I wish that Harpo and Chico could be here to share with me this great honor,\" he said, naming the two deceased brothers (Zeppo and Gummo were still alive at the time). Groucho also praised the late [[Margaret Dumont]] as a great straight woman who never understood any of his jokes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a1YsAxiiH98 |title=Groucho Marx receiving an Honorary Oscar\u00ae |publisher=Oscars.org |date=2009-11-24 |accessdate=2018-08-17}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1921|| ''[[Humor Risk]]'' || Watson || Short, lost\n|-\n|1925|| ''[[Too Many Kisses]]'' || The Village Peter Pan ||